Title: 2019 Lamborghini Urus 4.0 Auto AWD 5dr
Description:
Registered on 13/02/2019

One of the world’s fastest SUVs. The Lamborghini Urus is what happens when the maker of the planet’s most outlandish supercars turns its hand to a large five-door family car with proper ground clearance and off-road ability. The Urus has the 4.0-litre twin-turbo charged V8 producing 641bhp and 627lb ft of torque (from just 2,250rpm) ,the  torque is just absolutely amazing and gives you a thrilling rib-crushing feeling. The power is always there whenever you need it, whatever ratio you find yourself in the eight-speed auto. Also the urus woofles and rumbles making the hairs stand up on the back of your neck , its an absolutely incredible sound giving you a harder blare as you approach the limiter there are crackles and pops on downshifts and a lovely sounding flair on startup, the acceleration is just rapid.

The Lamborghini Urus has cutting edge , distinct and streamlined design with multiple souls. Sporty ,elegant and off road. Its muscular surfaces make it appear strong and self secure , while the beautiful 23″ Taigete rims  allow a luxury super sports car look. All the surfaces are designed with a clear attention to functionality. Its also wider than many full size SUVs such as the range rover , and its aluminium bodywork wears enough creases and gaping air intakes to remind onlookers that Lamborghini is, above all else a maker shamelessly brash supercars.

complimented by an interior of Nero Ade with Giallo Taurus Stitching. Fitted with a number of options including , Brake Calipers in Yellow, Lamborghini Anima with Off-Road Modes, Black Matt Exhaust Tailpipes, Style Pack, Panoramic Roof, Head-Up Display, Advanced 3D Bang and Olufsen Sound System, DAB Radio, SatNav System, Heated Front and Rear Seats, Full Electric Comfort Ventilated Massage Seats in Leather with Q-citura, Top View Camera, Embroidered Lamborghini Shield on Headrest and more. On the centre consul there is an ‘Ego’ leaver and ‘Anaemia’ leaver. If you were to activate the ‘Ego’ it fine tunes the vehicle dynamics including steering, traction and suspension adjustments to make the ideal driving mode for how you want to drive This mode is entirely configurable and it’s all about you. On the ‘Anaemia’ leaver is the key command to choose the desired setup so the vehicle adapts to the according driving mode selected. If you are looking for a sporty , elegant off road vehicle While there’s genuinely space for the whole family, plus lots of space for a slightly terrified dog in the boot then this could be for you.

Title: 2017 Ferrari 488 Spider 3.9
Description:
Registered on the 12/06/2017. The 488.
Where to start with this car? Every single aspect of this car is meticulously engineered and just inconceivably incredibly. There are so many little features and quirks to talk about but I’m going to do my best at summarising and giving you a clear idea of how amazing this car really is.
Let’s start with the looks. True beauty. The 488 and its predecessor, the 458 are two of the most gorgeous cars ever built. I mean, just look at it. Admiring it brings goosebumps to your skin and makes you feel giddy because its looks are just so exciting! Finished in Rosso Corsa (“Ferrari Red” – the only colour a Ferrari really should be…) which only more enhances the excitability of this car because everyone loves a red Ferrari! The stunning body lines, the 20″ wheels, the LED headlights, the circular tail lights and large dual exhaust pipes. All moulded to absolute perfection.
In terms of quality and attention to detail, the inside is no different from the outside. Again, everything has been meticulously engineered and crafted to be flawless. The Italians are known for their impeccable leather skills and doesn’t it just show! Everything is wrapped in leather and stitched with contrasting stitching and I think you’ll agree that it is a genuine work of art. The 488 also has one of the coolest features we’ve ever seen in a car and that’s the passenger display. It shows all the information that the driver gets in his gauge cluster and you can cycle through different screen including, the speed you’re going, the maximum speed this particular car has travelled, the average speed, the trip odometer, the time you’ve been travelling and also a screen showing various performance level readouts in live time!
Just behind your seat is your 3.9 litre twin-turbocharged V8 that will send you from 0-60 in 3 seconds flat. Just let that sink in. 1,2,3 and you’re at 60mph. The power is addictive and, quite frankly, terrifying – in a good way… Any gear, any rpm, instantaneous, ridiculous power. The 458 had all the power you needed but the 488 is on another level. The gearbox is just phenomenal. It’s so smooth and quick and the noise of every gear change will put a smile on your face. Speaking of noise, everyone will be looking at your car when you drive past because the sound that comes from that engine and that exhaust is just wonderful in every way.
Ridiculously Ferrari.

Title: 2018 Ferrari GTC4 Lusso T 3.9 V8
Description:
Registered on the 19-07-2018.
A supercar with 4 genuinely useable seats. Sounds like madness doesn’t it? Well, not anymore because the legendary company called Ferrari (ever heard of them?) has made it possible.
But before we get into that, let’s just clear ourselves up on what this car is classified as. It is actually classified as a hatchback! And the proper terminology for that ever so unique yet beautiful shape is a “shooting-brake.” It is stunning. Instantly recognisable as a supercar from its extremely long bonnet, its carbon cooling vents, black quad exhaust pipes, its large front splitter and that insane rear diffuser. Now, if you’ve got a moment, just admire the photos of the cars and try to really get a feel for how indescribably gorgeous this car is.
Driving any Ferrari is an experience like no other. The noise of the engine, the low seating position, the looks you get as you drive past, but this one is just something else… You can genuinely drive this car every day without compromising on too much. You can actually go to the shop and get all your shopping in the boot, you can have 4 people in the car and still be able to hit over 170mph and you can do all of this without being shaken around the cockpit because the suspension is adjustable from soft to sport! It is so intuitive and completely changes the idea of a supercar.
The Italian’s are known for their impeccable leather skills. Everything is finished perfectly and yes, “perfectly” get used loosely but in a Ferrari, you can take the meaning literally. The door cards, the seats and the dash are absolutely divine. There is nothing quite like it and if you delve into the finer details you will realise that every single tiny little aspect of this interior has been thoroughly thought out and planned for flawlessness. Now, my favourite “finer detail” would have to be the passenger information screen. It is a £3,000 optional extra that entails a small screen being installed on the passenger side and it gives them the ability to see some super unique information like; the music that’s playing, a compass telling you which direction you’re going, what gear your driver is in, how fast you’re going, what g-forces you’re pulling and even what driving mode the car is in. You can expect many many features like this in the GTC 4 Lusso T…

Title: 2013 Ferrari 458 (570ps) Spider Convertible 2d Auto Seq.
Transmission: Auto Sequential with Filo Speciale Giallo Coloured Special Stitching
Description:
Registered on 10/03/2013

If you’re a diehard driving purist with a budget that knows no bounds, look no further than the 2013 Ferrari 458.

Just gripping the steering wheel makes you feel like you’ve somehow mistakenly slipped onto a Formula 1 car. Hit the big Red engine start button and the noise that comes out of those triple pipes is like no other on the planet.  4.5L V8 spinning into life is mesmerising.

The V8 is hooked up to a seven-speed twin clutch Getrag transmission that operates as an auto, or you can change gears with the large, steering wheel mounted change paddles.

Wielding that F1-like steering wheel requires but the gentlest of grips, the steering seemingly effortless, yet incredibly precise.

Various drive modes are accessed through the Manettino flip switch affixed to the steering wheel, from wet to sport to full off for the traction system.

Reverse is engaged via a button at the the foot of the centre instrument console and there is even a button for raising the front of the car so it doesn’t scrape over driveways. The JBL audio system is secreted somewhere behind the dash and the controls are accessible only though the right hand of the two computer screens which doubles as a huge digital speedometer.

EXTERIOR
The exterior is finished in Nero Daytona! with some subtle Giallo Coloured striping.

INTERIOR
The interior is upholstered Nero Alcantara, Carpets in Extracampionario with Filo Speciale Giallo Coloured Special Stitching really complements the Nero exterior with Giallo Brake Calipers.

Title: 2010 Ferarri 458 Italia
Description:
Powered by the 4.5-liter V8, the 458 Italia makes 563BHP at 9000 rpm and ( 398 ft-lbs ) of torque at 6000 rpm, enabling a 0-60 mph time of 3.3 seconds which is heart stoppingly fast. It is at this point you turn on the ignition, thumb the big red starter button on the left-hand side of the steering wheel, and remember why god saw fit to bless humanity with the Ferrari V8. The 458 Italia sounds like an F1 car with its balls dropped. It purrs into life with a velvety rumble that sounds like a slight fast idle – no chugging and a couple of quick blips see the revs snap to attention and fall away with the speed you can only associate with the natural aspiration.The Italia becomes a pleasant little alchemist of sensation, spins a web filled with immediate, simple joy. Then there are the inlet wings. These angle air upwards so enough is pushed through the radiators at low speeds but they then deform to reduce drag at higher speeds, when you don’t need such a large inlet area for adequate cooling. These wings also generate downforce. Also the vents below the rear lights are for radiators to cool the gearbox and clutch.

Beyond its sexy exterior and head-turning growl, the Italia is, at its root, a very good means of transport. The 458’s cabin is spacious for two and is well dressed in the finest leathers with surprisingly very comfortable special coloured Giallo modena stitching seats, extra ample head, leg, and shoulder room, and a level of quality to its build and materials surpassed only by the truly hyper luxurious. The protruding, almost abstract-looking vents give the dashboard the appearance of wrapping around the driver, and with most of the controls placed on the steering wheel or to the right of the driver, it is an extremely driver-focused cabin .However, luggage space, restricted to what you can fit under the bonnet, is actually quite good for such a manically focused car.

SPECIFICATION

Title: 2018 ASTON MARTIN V8 VANTAGE COUPE ZF
Description:
First registered – 15/12/2018

This latest Vantage is the first Aston Martin developed from start to finish under the company’s new leadership team – and it shows. The brand is a brilliant British success story and the Vantage a fantastically well-rounded sports car.

Let’s start with the design. It looks stunning from behind, with a majestically rising rear spoiler and delightfully detailed lights. It’s a little plainer at the shark-nosed (and slightly Lightning McQueen-esque) front, but proportionally it’s absolutely perfect.

The cabin covered in luxurious leather and typical Aston detailing. The new Vantage is simply sensational.

Under the skin, the Vantage shares much with the DB11. That includes the fabulous, Mercedes sourced 4.0-litre twin-turbo V8; tweaked and tuned in-house for what Aston feels are the right power characteristics. The noise is a little less shouty than in an AMG, too. This Engine will present you with 503bhp and 685Nm of torque, coupled with a ZF eight-speed automatic Gearbox.

Along with double-wishbone suspension at the front, the Vantage uses a solid subframe and multi-link set-up at the rear, offering more of a connection to the road. There’s also an electronic differential.

The driving position is spot on with plenty of adjustment to make you feel totally connected to the controls.

In edition to a highly spec from factory, this car also comes with the following options.

 

Aston Martin Premium Audio, Sports plus Package, Sports plus Seats, Electric steering Column, New Vaned Front Grill, Rear Clear smoked lights, Sports exhaust Package,

Title: 2021 Audi RSQ8 4.0 TFSI V8 Carbon Black Tiptronic Quattro
Model: RSQ8 4.0 TFSI V8 Carbon Black Tiptronic Quattro
Description:
First Registered – 22/01/2021

This is a full-house RS model, so gets the same lunatic 4.0-litre twin-turbo V8 petrol engine as the RS6 estate… producing 592bhp and 590lb ft of torque. That means 0-62mph in 3.8 seconds, 0-124mph in 13.7 seconds, and a limited top speed of 155mph. Insert wide-eye emoji here.

If the RSQ8 is your thing and you’re looking for a way to justify it, you could argue that its superior ground clearance, air suspension that’s height-adjustable by 90mm, hill-descent control and commanding view of the road is a few easy options to help with the justification.

The RSQ8 is an astonishing piece of engineering.

Standard equipment is comprehensive, as you’d expect for its six-figure price point, so pretty much all of Audi’s trademark features are included – matrix LED headlights, 22-inch alloy wheels, Audi’s top-drawer heated, ventilated and electrically operated sports seats, a full suite of interior displays made up of the usual virtual cockpit and dual-touchscreen MMI systems. You get the point.

This Model Being the, the aforementioned Carbon Black model swaps out the standard 22-inch wheels for a set of 23-inch items, a sports exhaust system and, as its name might suggest, a liberal application of carbonfibre trim components inside and out.

This car has recently had the A Service carried out at main dealer.

Title: 2007 Ferrari F430 4.3 V8
Description:
Registered on 14/06/2007. The incredibly iconic F430. Elegantly finished in the true Ferrari colour of Rosso Corsa with beautiful Creme leather electric seats and Rosso red carpets. This car is genuinely stunning from every single angle and the sound of the quad-pipe exhaust system is intoxicating. Driving this car is an astounding experience and will put a smile on your face everytime you push the throttle/start button. With electronic systems based on Ferrari’s dominating F1 cars, this car gives an immensely close feeling of what it’s like to be in an F1 Drivers shoes. An incredible asset to own and one that will never fail to empower your emotions.
This will be serviced by Ferarri on point of sale.

Electric seats, F1 paddle shift, central locking, ABS, power steering, traction control, airbags, climate control, 19″ alloy wheels.

Title: 2015 Porsche 911 (991) Turbo S Coupe (PDK)
Description:
Registered on 10/06/2015.

This is easily one of the most beautiful cars on the road. The plethora of elegant body lines, each one of them so smooth and expertly moulded to perfection.

The colour combination of this car is Arguably one of the best! Fitted with an extent of factory options increasing the desirability and the residual value.

The Gloss Black Factory fitted Aero Pack makes a huge difference to the cosmetic look of the car that came with a cost of £5,000.00.

Onto the inside. It really is a well specc’d, attractive interior and it’s such a lovely place to be. The heated and vented sports seats are wrapped in soft, perforated leather, they’re electrically adjustable with memory functions and have Porsche logos embossed into the headrests.  Your infotainment system has everything you’d expect in a car of this nature; reversing camera, front and rear parking sensors, Radio, CD player, SatNav, Bluetooth Phone Connection and all your car’s system settings. Lastly, if you look up when sat in the car, you’ll see the gorgeous panoramic sunroof option with tilt and slide function, which also lets a great amount of natural light into the cabin making a big difference.

This car drives incredibly well. The PDK gearbox is just phenomenal, every shift feels instantaneous and silky smooth – I’d go as far as to say unnoticeable! The power is instant. The 3.8Litre Twin Turbo will deliver a whopping amount of power and is ready to be offered at anytime… 580 horses by the way… This is a car that is capable of speeds of over 200MPH (claimed 205) Please, do not try this at home.

Thanks to the Sports Chrono Pack, there are different drive modes that you can switch between depending on your situation – Normal, Sport, Sport Plus and individual. These modes all change the way your car drives by tightening suspension, sharpening the throttle response and tightening the steering. The adjustability is endless and therefore you’ll never get bored! One other thing that Porsche has perfected in this car is the art of active aerodynamics that keeps your car glued to the road around any corner at high speeds.
An everyday supercar that will continue to amaze you.

The car has just had a major service at a Porsche main dealer. and has 18 Months Porsche Main dealer warranty that will come with the car.

Auto Start/Stop, Burmester Sound System, Alcantara Headlining, Dual-zone Climate Control, Cruise Control, Auto Headlights, Electric Windows, Rear Wiper Option, Turbo S Sill Plates.

Title: 2014 Porsche 911 (991) Turbo S 3.8  PDK AWD 2dr
Description:
Registered on the 17/12/2014. Ridiculous, Ludicrous, Madness.
The new 911 Turbo S. It’s faster and more beautiful than ever. Just look at 20″ 911 Turbo S Alloy Wheels Painted Black with Diamond Cut Finish and the plethora of elegant body lines, each one of them so smooth and expertly moulded to perfection. The circular headlights with the 4 bright LED daytime running lights and that beautiful wave-like spoiler that elegantly flows down from the roof to create that beautiful “Porsche” look. This specific Turbo S is fitted with an amazing sounding Akrapovic exhaust system and a carbon fibre rear diffuser. What a masterpiece.
As standard with any Porsche, this car drives unbelievably. The PDK gearbox is just phenomenal. Every shift feels instantaneous and incredibly smooth. The power is instant. Any time you want to gain any sort of speed, in any gear, the full amount of power that the 911 can deliver is right under your right foot. All 580 horses. Thanks to the Sports Chrono Pack, there are different drive modes that you can switch between depending on your situation – Normal, Sport, Sport Plus and individual. These modes all change the way your car drives by tightening suspension, sharpening throttle response and tightening steering. The adjustability is endless. One other thing that Porsche has perfected in this car is the art of active aerodynamics that keeps your car glued to the road around any corner at high speeds.
On the inside of this incredibly powerful track and road demon, there is a beautiful interior. Carbon Fibre Race seats, a gorgeous leather-wrapped steering wheel, soft carpets and carbon fibre pieces everywhere. Porsche have this impeccable standard that they abide by and that’s what really makes a Porsche. Take one look at this car, from any angle, and you will fall absolutely in love.
Last but not least…A top speed of 205MPH.
What more could you possibly ask for?

Title: 2011 Lamborghini Gallardo LP550-2 Coupe 5.2 V10 E-Gear
Description:
Registered on the 21/07/2011.
Mr Valentino Balboni. If you’ve never heard of him, let me briefly enlighten you. Balboni started at Lamborghini as an apprentice all the way back in 1968 and was soon after asked, by Ferruccio Lamborghini himself, to work with Bob Wallace and test drive the Lamborghinis that had been in for service and help develop and perfect the drive of the new Lamborghinis. Valentino was heavily involved in the production of the Diablo, Murcielago and, obviously, the Gallardo. Balboni had such a strong relationship with Lamborghini that, after his departure from the company in 2008, they made a special car to commemorate his 40 years of service. He was also heavily involved in the production of the car and it was made to be a solely rear-wheel drive car to meet Balboni’s preference. Only 250 Balboni Gallardo’s were built but they sold out and were deemed a huge success so in 2011 they based these LP550-2’s on the Balboni Edition and were sold to the general public.
550hp to your rear wheels is something you have to ultimately respect but Lamborghini did implicate some very intelligent driver assistance systems and produced an extremely safe supercar. The experience driving one of these cars is just an utter privilege. It has everything that the average car doesn’t have, but it does have some very useful everyday features that you would find in your everyday car! The attention to detail is just phenomenal, the materials used are all of the absolute pinnacles of quality and when you start to push your right foot towards the floor, you are loudly reminded that this car is a driving masterpiece. Heads will turn as you drive past, alleyways will echo with the amazing sound coming from the rear and the smile will not leave your face until the vehicle is out of your sight.
Presented in Bianco Monocerus with full black leather seats. The specification includes a transparent engine cover, engine bay lighting, SatNav, Rear Camera, Bluetooth, Front Lifting Gear and the optional E-Gear automatic transmission option.

19″ Gloss Black Alloy Wheels, Gallardo Side Sills, Carbon Flat-Bottomed Steering Wheel, Diamond Stitched Leather Seats and Door Cards, Carbon Gauge Cluster, Carbon Centre Console, Steering Column Mounted Shifter Paddles, Sport and Corsa Mode, SatNav, Media, Radio and Car Info.

Title: 2019 Porsche Cayman 718 GT4 Clubsport 4.0 Manual.
Description:
Registered on 01-11-2019

This car benefits from full PPF ensuring it has remained in showroom condition., The exterior Black paintwork is complimented by the Satin Aurum GT4 Alloy Wheels, Yellow Painted Brake Callipers along with the upgraded lightweight ceramic Disc brakes (£6,000 option). Black Porsche & GT4 Logos, Smoked Rear Taillights and Black Painted Sports Exhaust.The suspension comes from the more expensive 911 GT3, with switchable adaptive dampers fitted as standard, Stepping inside you are greeted by a Black Leather & Alcantara interior with 918 Style Carbon Fibre Bucket Seats (£8,000 option), Grey Contrasting Stitch, black Seatbelts, Sports Chrono, Alcantara Steering Wheel, Reversing Camera, Carbon Fibre Interior Package and Touchscreen Infotainment. , The 4.0L Naturally Aspirated Flat-Six paired with the 6-Speed Manual transmission, RWD Set-Up and 414 horses, ensures that the GT4 is a proper driver’s car!

Remainder of Porsche warranty. This really is an unbelievable car!

Title: 2011 Mclaren MP4-12C
Description:
Registered on the 01/10/2011. What a beautiful machine. Every angle, every line and every aspect of this car is empowering.
The monstrous V8 twin-turbocharged engine will shoot you from 0-60 in just 3.2 seconds and can propel you to a ridiculous top speed of 204mph. The 12C is equipped with an absurdly quick shifting dual-clutch automatic transmission, an incredible traction control system, independent suspension for every wheel and insane aerodynamics. Mclaren has also implemented an active rear spoiler which will raise under intense braking. These aspects all add up to a perfectly engineered supercar that makes you realize why Mclaren are one of best teams in Formula 1 Racing.
To enter the 12C you have to slide your hand under the door in just the right way and then the door will open upwards. The interior of this car is impressively unique with carbon fibre accents and an angled centre touchscreen where you’ll find your SatNav, Media Controls, Vehicle settings/status and Radio. Continuing with the unique topic, the climate controls are mounted on the door cards with a digital dial displaying your temperature. Only the top materials were going to be used in this car and that’s why the seats and dash are leather and the headliner is a gorgeous Alcantara.
True beauty expertly engineered into an unbelievable vehicle.
You may be wondering why this car stands out so much more than the Normal 12c. This has been fitted with the all Famous Gemballa KIt, Gemballa is German car manufacturer with over 34 years of experience in refining and individualization of Porsche and McLaren sports cars.

A great opportunity to own a one-off supercar.

Title: 2005 Lamborghini Gallardo 5.0 V10
Description:
Registered 01/03/2005. Lamborghini’s best selling and most recognisable supercar. Presented in the stunning pearl yellow with gorgeous black, yellow stitched, heated seats and 19″ beautiful upgraded alloy wheels.
Turn the key in the Gallardo and you are greeted by the ferocious sound of the monstrous V10.
This car is simply outstanding and will not fail to have you grinning from ear to ear.
And as you would expect with only 8,000 miles, this car is as good as the day it left the showroom.
An appreciating supercar.

ABS, Climate Control, Electric Mirrors, Electric Windows, Remote Locking, Steering Wheel Rake and Reach Adjustment, Traction Control.

Title: 2020 BMW X5 M Competition 5dr Step Auto
Description:
FIRST REGISTERED – 01/12/2020

The Comp’s twin-turbo’d 4.4-litre V8 is remapped up to 616bhp,  torque remains pegged at 553lb ft.

Engage launch control and the X5 M dispatches 0-62mph in 3.8 seconds. Should you be minded to get to 124mph, this super truck of oomph will blast you there in 13.4 seconds, Spend £2,100 on the optional M Driver’s Package (which this has) and your top speed leaps from 155mph to 190mph.

This monsterwagen is very nearly as quick as the likes of a Lamborghini Urus or Bentley Bentayga Speed. It’s just as well-equipped, seats the same number of people in space and comfort, but £100k + cheaper. (can we utter the word cheap in this sentence)

Underneath, very little standard X5 remains. The M’s engine mounts are beefier, as are the suspension foundations. You get adaptive dampers with body-roll counteraction. The cooling and oil systems are approved for racetrack use. There’s more camber, fatter tyres, enormous brakes and you can even change the feel through the brake pedal, for no good reason we can think of, but its very cool non the same.

Those M1 and M2 favourite-settings keys will come in handy if you want to exploit this lunatic’s enormous reserves of computing power.  A world-class engine and supercar-tuned suspension.

The X5 M Comp’s interior is what really sells us on this vehicle’s overall styling. The beige leather buckets, with quilted beige inserts and colored “X5 M” badges in the headrest, are very good looking. The standard 12.3-inch central touchscreen flows (almost) seamlessly into the 12.3-inch digital instrument cluster, the two massive screens giving off a very high-tech look. And among the beige leather, black accents, and aluminum trim pieces, three red buttons stand out: M1 and M2 drive modes on the upper part of the steering wheel, and the red ignition button – the latter looks like something designed for a missile launch. It’s this attention to detail that makes the inside of the X5 M Competition so alluring.

The car has more spec than a NASA space Rocket equipped for Mars, the X5 M has navigation, Wi-Fi, gesture control, a head-up display, the “Hey BMW” voice assistant, wireless charging, and wireless Apple CarPlay, Reversing camera’s and much much more.

Title: 2015 Audi R8 5.2 FSI V10 PLUS quattro 610 PS S tronic 2dr
Model: R8 5.2 FSI V10 PLUS quattro 610 PS S tronic 2dr
Description:
Registered on the 13/11/15.

The Audi R8. Starting out in 2006 and becoming instantly successful due to its driveability and easiness to live with on a daily basis, unlike most other supercars. In 2015 the all-new R8 came out and what a car it is…

I mean, just look at it, stunning from every angle. The gaping honeycomb front grille, the laser-like headlights and aerodynamic fins underneath all scream aggression! Moving to the side, you’ll see some really drastic but beautiful body lines directing air into the carbon side vents to cool that monster under the glass… And finally the rear, quad rectangular exhaust pipes, more grilles with aero fins, a beautiful full carbon fibre spoiler and one of the most insane rear diffusers on the market! It’s a work of automotive art and it only gets better from here…

Audi’s lower-end car interiors are lovely as it is so when they made this supercar, they knew they had to step it up a notch… Gorgeous Nappa leather sports seats, a perforated flat-bottomed multifunctional steering wheel with a bright red ‘Engine Start’ button that awakes the beast behind your seat. Aluminium shifter paddles, a lovely set of rubber topped sports pedals and the matte carbon inserts scattered around look fantastic. But the best part of the interior is definitely the driver’s dash. “Virtual Cockpit,” is Audi’s name for it and it’s a full HD infotainment system that’s completely customizable. The navigation tab actually shows a google map image of where you are! You can see pretty much anything you want, projected right in front of you so you never have to take your eyes far from the road. It’s the most advance gauge cluster technology in the car market today.

Now onto the ridiculous capabilities of this car.
A 5.2-litre, wonderful sounding V10 engine, 602hp, 0-60 in 3.2 seconds and a top speed of a staggering 205 mph… Audi’s world-renowned Quattro all-wheel-drive system keeps you planted to the ground through any corner and can send 100% of power to each axel independently. The 7-speed twin-clutch automatic transmission is absolutely flawless and shifts in milliseconds and when doing so, a glorious noise exits the exhaust. The power feels endless as you soar through the rev range and as you occasionally look down at your tac, you’ll see the numbers climbing rapidly too. Obviously, the faster you go, the more stopping power you need and that’s why this car is fitted with a set of 15″ carbon-ceramic brake disks on the front and 14″ on the rear. Think about that, 15 inches of brake disk! And oh yeah, the front callipers have 6 pistons pushing your pads to that disk – slamming on these brakes would be like crashing into a solid brick wall…

Incredible looks, intelligent technology and insane performance from you engineers at Audi

Sport Plus Pack, Sport Exhaust System, Audi Magnetic Ride, Dynamic Steering, Carbon Package, Cruise Control, Front and Rear Parking Sensors With Reverse Camera, Electric Folding Mirrors and Advanced Key.

Lat Serviced @13,300 miles on 7th September 2018 with 4 new Bridgestone Tyres.

Title: 2018 Range Rover Sport 5.0 V8 SVR Auto 4WD (s/s) 5dr
Description:
This 2018 Land Rover Range Rover Sport 5.0 SVR has a stunning specification coming with over £12,000 in extras, Specced with Heads up Display, Extended Carbon Fibre Trim Finisher, SVR Carbon Fibre Exterior Pack with Exposed Carbon Bonnet, Heated and Cooled front seats with Heated rear seats, Privacy Glass, Sliding Glass Panoramic Sunroof & 22″ 5 split spoke Alloys, this really is a one of a kind spec!

Is there much of a difference from the older model?

They have cleaned up the design a little and added some extra kit. But SVO division managed to squeeze even more power out of the 5.0-litre supercharged V8 in the SVR – namely 24bhp and 14lb ft. That meant a drop in the sprint time by 0.3sec to 4.3 seconds and 12mph added to the top speed now totalling 174mph. You know that wide-eyed, jaw-dropping reaction you make in the midst of a fierce thunderstorm when lightning strikes? It feels, and indeed sounds, just like that – when it’s in Dynamic mode, anyway. The sports exhaust system accentuates the supercharged V8 as much as it can – bellowing under hard throttle, farting like a spoiled brat blowing raspberries on upshifts and dumping big globs of fuel into the exhaust just for the hell of it when coasting. With the sports exhaust on its exentric but it’s so, so addictive.

For such a big vehicle, does it handle?

It’s no 991 turbo around the bends, but not that far off. Even if this is the fire-breathing model, the Range Rover Sport is still built for wafty comfort rather than out-and-out dynamics. Switch it to Dynamic mode and there’s admirable body control without ruining the ride, a weighty steering rack that’s smooth but borders on feeling overly-artificial, and all-wheel drive that will pull you out of almost any hard corner situation.

How about the interior?

The Range Rover Sport now uses the same interior design setup first seen on the Velar, so there’s a twin Touch Pro Duo infotainment system named. An upper screen controls nav, entertainment and phone connectivity while a lower screen is reserved for climate control, seating settings and the drive mode select. Range Rover SVR’s interior is a clean blend of ultra-modern touches and some very clever little details. Material quality is really impressive.

Title: 2020 Audi RS7 4.0 TFSI V8 Carbon Black Tiptronic quattro
Model: RS7 4.0 TFSI V8 Carbon Black Tiptronic quattro
Description:
First registered 19/06/2020

With a 4.0-litre, twin-turbocharged V8 making 592bhp and 590lb ft this is a Supercar Challenger.

3.6 secs 0-62mph, With a top speed of 155mph (unless derestricted) to 174mph

An eight-speed automatic gearbox is standard, as is Quattro permanent four-wheel drive along with all-wheel steering, which can send up to 70% of power to the front wheels and up to 85% to the rears depending on driving conditions and drive mode.

Audi Sport has worked hard to turn it into a performance flagship worthy of its place as the top RS four-door.

Audi has brought out the big guns, with bigger wheels, tyres and brakes than have ever been seen on a performance model such as this, not to mention active differentials and Audi’s clever hydraulically cross-linked dampers.

To accommodate all this new tech the RS7 has also been given a bespoke body, further separating it from the standard A7 while also acting as a clear statement of intent that this RS7 is not going to be the afterthought executive express it once was.

it is fully loaded from the outset,  laser-assisted matrix LED headlights and all the other usual high-end German-car fodder. In terms of performance hardware, RS7s ride on adaptive air suspension as standard, with Audi’s Sport Differential also standard fit. The Carbon Sport upgrades are mostly aesthetic, with carbon inlays, grey detailing inside and larger 22-inch wheels.

Inside, it’s Amazing what Audi have done, in addition to the standard model you get Valcona and Alcantara-trimmed sports seats, Audi’s Virtual Cockpit digital instrument cluster and a flat-bottomed wheel. There’s also the Audi Drive Select button and RS mode selector on the steering wheel, as well as a Performance setting on the Virtual cockpit.

Title: 2011 Bentley Continental 6.0 FlexFuel GTC Supersports Auto 4WD 2dr
Description:
Registered – 22/06/2011
Bentley’s Continental Supersports Convertible takes the flex-fuel, high-performance Supersports specification and applies it to that sun-loving celebrity’s favourite, the Continental GTC convertible.
Supercar performance without the loss of practicality and comfort. Finished in the Stunning Gloss black accompanied with these 20 Black wheels covering them huge ceramic Brakes really makes this car look amazing. By no means does the amazement stop there. The interior makes you feel like you’re royalty with the black leather/alcantara cross-stitched seats, which will happily massage you on request with the touch of a button. Bentley didn’t miss out on the everyday features such as satellite navigation, a rearview camera and Bluetooth, which plays through their fantastic Naim Premium Audio System. Bentley’s attention to detail is exquisite. All the stitching is done by hand and the Bentley logo embroiled into the head rests really makes you know you’re driving something special.
The Bentley feels terrific. The steering is surprisingly light, wonderfully precise. The car rides with a firm control, connected but sophisticated enough to filter out unnecessary information, but it’s the way it responds to direction changes that is truly surprising.The front and rear of the car are so in tune that the Supersports seems to do everything just as you ask it, no slack, all of a piece. And it’s so easy to drive. Considering under the bonet is the sledgehammer 6.0-litre W12, all 621bhp and 590lb ft of it. Bentley claims 0-60mph in 4-seconds and 202mph. When this car came out it was the fastest four-seater convertible in the world.
2 owner car and all serviced at Bentley Manchester. Last service 3,000 miles ago.

If you’re considering buying this car, you probably should!

Model: Atego 822 RS Evolution X2 Race Cruiser 7.5t

Title: 2013 Aston Martin V8 Vantage S
Description:
First registered – 29/05/2013

Influenced by Aston Martin’s GT4 racecar, the V8 Vantage S is designed to offer greater dynamic capability compared with the regular model. Offered as a coupe or roadster, the car shares its 4.7-litre V-8 with the V8 Vantage, but the engine has been tuned to produce 430 hp and 361 pounds-feet of torque. A seven-speed automated manual transmission, controlled by steering-wheel-mounted paddle shifters, is the only transmission available. Pushing the standard Sport button quickens gear changes, increases throttle response and opens bypass valves in the exhaust system.

The V8 Vantage S features different springs and dampers, and it has unique stability system tuning. Exterior cues include a carbon fibre front splitter and wide side sills.

For this facelift 2013 model, the V8 Vantage S gains new standard features like rain-sensing wipers, automatic headlights and a reversing camera. A sport suspension was a new no-cost option.

Standard features include navigation, satellite radio, front and rear parking sensors, cruise control and Bluetooth connectivity. Also, a new seven-speed automatic gearbox was welcomed.

This is a brand new conversion which has never ever been slept in,

All Volkswagen the T28 Transporter models are powered by the 2.0-litre, four-cylinder TDI diesel engine which produces 150bhp and 35mpg in return. The Transporter continues to be a hugely impressive performer on the road, particularly in terms of its ride comfort. The Transporter puts its driver in a high, upright position similar to that which you’d find in larger panel vans from the class above and quite different from the more car-like approach but You get a very good commanding view of the road ahead and easy access, with the main controls all well-positioned once you are inside.

On the exterior the Transporter is finished in a lovely Indium grey which really does look stunning from all angles followed by the red pin stripes at the front which really does give the Volkswagen Transport a lovely sporty touch as it matches up beautifully with the red brake callipers. Underneath it has been tastefully lowered on 40mm lowering spring which gives the T6 a stunning stance.

It’s inside, however, where the changes are most keenly felt. The latest VW infotainment system now features technology straight out of the brand’s passenger cars, and the new electronic steering system allows for a variety of advanced safety kit to appear on the Transporter for the first time. Connectivity is also a big part of the T6.1’s appeal, as all models now come with a fully integrated SIM card. Title: Jaguar F-Type 5.0 V8 Supercharged
Description:
Registered on the 29/09/2013

The most incredible sounding V8.
From some angles, the F-Type has an amazing sense of elegance but from others, it screams aggression. There’s a deep rumble and firecracker soundtrack on the overrun, and the V8’s unique quad tailpipes provide a different kind of aural treat. This car really does look exquisite.
To drive this car is an immensely thrilling experience. The 5.0 Supercharged engine is effortlessly rapid, sprinting from 0-60mph in 4.2 seconds The lightning-quick gear changes, the perfectly weighted steering, and the astonishing grip all bundled together and driven by and an impeccable V8 engine. All 488bhp will leave you breathless. Jaguar gives you a different driving mode and an exhaust note changing button to make the drive even more exciting.
The interior of this car is just as stunning as the outside looks and the driving capabilities. With Heated/electrically adjustable full leather seats, a leather multifunctional steering wheel, delightful dials and all the media options, you could wish for. A car you don’t want to miss out on.

The beautifully British Jaguar F-Type.

This car was bought brand new in South Africa and has been brought to the island with its keeper roughly 4 years ago, Its condition is as new.As you would expect for such little mileage.
This car will be fully serviced before delivery.
Start/Stop Button, LED Daytime Running Lights, Retractable Rear Spoiler, Retractable Door Handles, Electric Parking Brake, Sports Suspension and 8″ Touch Screen. Rear view camera.

Title: 2021 Toyota Yaris GR Bespoke Red Bull Design
Model: Yaris GR Bespoke Red Bull Design
Description:
First registered – 21/07/2021

This is a completely Bespoke Red Bull Racing Livery Yaris GR, in addition the this awesome wrap this car has also had a set of 18″OZ Racing alloys fitted.

To add to the stance, lowering springs and a splitter kit have been fitted. The extended 2 Tier Roof spoiler helps finish off this awesome machine.

with the outside looking its best, then we need some sounds to go with it. A Full Milltek exhaust system along with uprated induction is like music to your ears.

The Toyota Yaris GR has to be one of the most anticipated cars of recent times.
We can’t think of a modern performance car that has generated more hype surrounding its arrival.
Powered by a 1.6litre turbocharged 3 cylinder engine, the most powerful one in the world.
The only choice is a six-speed manual Gearbox, and the 4WD system is claimed to be the lightest on the market. Lightest, but not most basic. There’s an aluminium central transfer case and in Normal mode, the torque is split 60:40 front to rear. That alters depending on the mode you choose. Sport is 30:70 and Track 50:50. Skids or grip, you decide. At the rear, there’s an electronically controlled clutch pack to divide torque between the wheels.

This car comes with the optional (£3,500) circuit pack, bringing those key changes under the skin that make the best use of the GR’s sweet little chassis. These include larger brakes, forged Enkei wheels with Michelin PS 4 rubber (Dunlops are standard), a stiffer suspension tune and a locking differential on both axles.
The whole thing weighs 1,280kg, is good for 0-62mph in 5.5secs and a 143mph top end.

This car has to be driven to make you believe how incredible it actually is.
If you don’t believe me, come and see for yourself.

Title: 2016 BMW M3 (Individual Frozen Pearl White) DCT 3.0 Twin Turbo
Model: M3 (Individual Frozen Pearl White) DCT 3.0 Twin Turbo
Description:
Registered – 30/03/2016

The First and most obvious thing to mention about this car is the Colour. It’s called Frozen pearl white and it’s absolutely gorgeous! This is an extremely rare option and needs to be seen to be fully appreciated.

This car has been very well-loved and maintained, with a fantastic main dealer service history with its most recent service/inspection having been completed within the last 10 miles.

The rear-wheel-drive M3 packs a turbocharged 3.0-litre inline six-cylinder engine that cranks out 425 hp and 406 pound-feet of torque. A seven-speed automated manual transmission (M-DCT) with steering-wheel-mounted paddle shifters will guide you through all of that power.

This car comes with a fantastic spec such as a Carbon Interior pack, some additional Carbon exterior options, Full leather electric seats. Memory drivers seats, Leather extended dash. Sat Nav, Reversing camera, Heated front seats, Heads up display. Harmon Kardon Sound. I

The driving section of the M experience starts with a push of a brake pedal and the press of a button. You hear the roar of the twin-turbocharged 3.0-litre straight-six engine that pushes an immense 425hp behind you. Everything about the M3’s mechanical being is made for incredible performance and handling but BMW has also given the M3 the ability to be a daily car. So essentially you have the best of both worlds! There are settings for your throttle response, suspension and steering weight and you can change them all from comfort to sport and to sport plus. Your usual BMW would have a button for changing the whole car’s characteristics from mode to mode but the M3 has the ability to change each individual aspect from mode to mode. And this is where the “M” buttons come in. On your steering wheel are buttons labelled “M1” and “M2”. You can customize these buttons in iDrive and set each driving aspect to your prefered mode so you can have your desired set-up at the quick push of a button!

A Car that needs to be seen to be fully appreciated.

Title: 2019 TESLA MODEL 3 – Standard Plus 4dr Auto
Description:
First registered – 12/11/2019

Safety is the most important part of every Tesla.  The Model 3 achieved NHTSA 5-star safety ratings in every category and subcategory.

The motor makes 235bhp and 277lb ft, so 0-60mph takes a still-brisk 5.3 seconds. The top speed is capped at 140mph. More than quick enough.

Tesla claims 254 miles of range, but in reality you’ll get closer to 220 miles from the 55kWh battery, which can be juiced at any CCS-compatible rapid charger (not just the company’s own Superchargers). A 7.4kWh wall-box will brim the battery in eight hours.

Inside the Model 3 really does feel like the future. The front cowl is low, so forward visibility is excellent (as is the sensation of speed). The driving position is good, and interior as well screwed-together as we’ve seen in any Tesla. They really are getting better.

The screen, which replaces basically every button you’d find in a normal car interior. It’s quick to respond and graphically very smart, It’s spacious, efficient, comfortable, reasonably-priced and well-equipped.

It still remains Tesla’s best car and a brilliant package overall.

This comes with a Tesla basic vehicle Warranty until November 2023, Battery limited warranty until November 2027 or 100,000 miles, and also a Drive unit Warranty until November 2023 or 100,000 miles.

The spec of this particular Model 3 is as follows,

AutoPilot

All Black interior

Midnight Silver Metallic\Partial premium interior

18″ Aero Wheels

Standard range plus rear wheel drive

Supercharger network access, Pay as you go.

Title: 2013 RANGE ROVER 3.0 TDV6 Vogue
Description:
First Registered – 08/10/2013

First class motoring.
Range Rovers used to be big boxy vehicles used on farms, and for military operations. How times have changed…

In the cabin you’ll find some gorgeous perforated leather heated and cooled memory seats with 16-way power adjustments, a soft leather-wrapped heated multifunctional steering wheel and just behind that, a fully digital dash showing your tachometer, speed and Range Rover’s Message centre where you can configure your vehicles settings, check for any warnings and check your vehicle’s service menu.
Your infotainment system is a large 8″ touchscreen that has touch capacitive buttons either side for quickly selecting the features you want to go to. Speaking of features, there’s plenty to play with including Bluetooth phone connectivity, Climate Control, SatNav, TV/Video all your vehicle status’ and settings.

The Panoramic Glass roof with the retractable folding blind when revealed allows a great amount of light into the cabin making it feel incredibly spacious.

Driving the Range Rover Vogue is such a comfortable experience. It’s so quiet in the cabin and the soft seats and suspension keep you cushioned from all the islands nasty potholes!
That 3.0 V6 starts up and your leather-surrounded gear selector slowly rises up out of its smooth position ready for you to select your drive mode. You put your foot on the aluminium rubber-topped brake pedal, select drive and then put both hands on your soft leather steering wheel, ready to go.

It might seem like all luxury and beautiful design but this car has ridiculous off-roading and handling capabilities. It’s fitted with air suspension to clear large obstacles and has Land Rover’s automatic all-terrain system that monitors the surface and alters the suspension and, through the 4 wheel drive system, sends the correct power to each wheel individually. You can also manually set the suspension to the type of surface you’re on. You don’t have to worry about overtaking and accelerating in such a large vehicle because this Range is fitted with the 4.4 diesel V8 which has just enough power to pull a house down! 335 hp and 516 ft-lb of torque to be exact…

The attention to detail, the endless amount of features, all under that incredible British name.

Title: 2018 BMW M2 3.0 Turbo DCT
Description:
Registered on 13/03/2018

A turbocharged 3.0-liter inline six-cylinder engine good for 365 horsepower.
What car!! Already an improvement from the first M2 ( who would have thought it was possible) A slight facelift, the kidneys grille’s are bigger, and the new teeth-sucking lower bumper has enlarged inlets to send cooling over the multiple-radiator system, taken from the M3/M4.

This M2 comes with the optional DCT semi-auto seven-speed transmission allowing gear changes to be incredibly fast and almost un noticeable.
It has slightly looser ESP, and modified software for the most fancy piece of tech in its chassis, an electronically controlled locking differential.

The BMW M2’s interior is all about achieving an authentic motorsport feel. It features the M specific instrument display with red dials and M2  welcome screen. It also lets you set individual driving profiles, while the shift paddles allow gear changes in a matter of seconds. To cap it off, it comes in premium Black Dakota leather with an illuminated M2 logo with the purple-blue-red triple stripe appearing on the seatbelts, Just looking at this car gets the pulse racing.

A very nicely Spec’d car including Sat Nav, Bluetooth, Heated seats, Electrically adjustable memory seats, Reversing camera.

Title: 2020 Ford Transit Custom 300Ltd MSRT Body Kit
Description:
First registered – 30/06/2020

This 2020 Ford Transit Custom is a mid-sized van that we have available in automatic transmission.

Noticeably this one looks a lot more appealing due to the very attractive MSRT body kit that’s been fitted and colour coded. Including Front and rear bumpers, side skirts and roof spoilers.

The van’s interior is spacious and well-designed, with plenty of storage space and comfortable seating. It also has a range of features, such as a touchscreen infotainment system, Sat nav, a rearview camera, and Bluetooth connectivity.

In terms of performance, the Ford Transit Custom Automatic has a smooth and responsive engine that provides good acceleration and fuel efficiency. The automatic transmission also provides seamless shifts, making it an easy vehicle to drive.

Overall, the Custom is a reliable and practical choice for businesses or individuals who need a mid-sized van for transporting goods.

Title: 2016 Jaguar F-PACE 3.0d V6 S 5dr Auto AWD
Description:
First registered – 02/08/2016

The F-Pace is Jaguar’s first-ever SUV, and the S model is the top-of-the-line variant. It’s a sleek and stylish crossover that combines sporty driving dynamics with practicality and comfort.

Of your diesel options, this is the more powerful F-Pace S, with a 3.0-litre V6. It produces 296bhp and 516 lb-ft of torque. That means a 150mph top speed and 5.8-second 0-60mph time It’s paired with an eight-speed automatic transmission that provides smooth and responsive shifts.

Behind the wheel, the F-Pace S feels agile and nimble, especially for a vehicle of its size. The steering is precise and well-weighted, and the suspension strikes a nice balance between sportiness and comfort. The adaptive dynamics system helps the car adjust to different driving conditions, making it a pleasure to drive on both twisty back roads and longer journeys.

The interior of the F-Pace S is elegant and modern, with high-quality materials and intuitive controls. The seats are supportive and comfortable, and there’s plenty of space for both passengers and cargo. The infotainment system is easy to use and features a large touchscreen display, as well as a variety of connectivity options.

Overall, the 2016 Jaguar F-Pace S is an impressive SUV that offers a winning combination of performance, style, and practicality. It’s a worthy competitor to other luxury crossovers in its class, and it’s definitely worth considering if you’re in the market for a high-end SUV.

Title: 2015 Audi RS3 Sportback 2.5 TFSI quattro 367 PS S tronic
Model: RS3 Sportback 2.5 TFSI quattro 367 PS S tronic
Description:
Registered on the 28/09/2015

One of The best hot hatch of them all With a huge specification.

Take one look at the RS3, from its large front air intakes to the massive tailpipes, and you know it’s ready to rock. Everything between and around those two features is stunning too: the sharp headlights, the chrome roof rails and mirror caps, those absolutely gorgeous 19″ 5-spoke alloy wheels and the way all 4 arches are perfectly flared. There are so many small, unique and amazing features on this car and describing them all would be impossible so if you have any interest in this car please come and see it and we’d be extremely happy to show you them all!
The inside is just as good as the outside. Just look at the seats! Diamond stitched, RS3 embossed heated leather seats. How great does that sound? The multifunctional flat-bottomed steering wheel is wrapped in Alcantara and leather.
A seven-speed dual-clutch automatic routes torque to all four wheels. The RS3 hits 60 mph in 3.5 seconds. It boasts a redline of 6900 rpm, and the rip of its distinctive exhaust note sounds amazing the whole way there and it also lets out an amazing burble between those magnificently quick gear changes.
Personally, i think Audi dominated the Market with this car.
Finished Sepang Blue, crystal effect with Comfort and sound package, Dynamic package, Audi Magnetic Ride, Sports exhaust system, Matt aluminium styling pack, Technology pack+Audi Connect, Electric interface for external use, AUX-IN jack, USB, and iPod
MMI navigation plus, Sport Bucket seats with Electric lumbar support, Fine Nappa leather/diamond quilt, beautifully finished carbon inlays.
This car needs to be driven to appreciate just how good it really is.

Title: 2019 Audi A4, 2.0 35 TFSI (150ps) Black Edition Saloon 4d S Tronic
Model: A4, 2.0 35 TFSI (150ps) Black Edition Saloon 4d S Tronic
Description:
Registered – 24/10/2019

The latest Audi A4 looks sharp on the outside and has one of the highest quality interiors in the executive car class.

This car is very visually pleasing, the White body has been broken up tastefully with the black roof, black mirror caps and side skirts along with the black edition two-tone wheels and the rear privacy. It’s powered by a 2litre turbo’d Petrol engine which produces 150bhp, as most modern-day cars you have the option to drive the car in different modes,  if your looking to be more economic, or fancy having a bit of fun, this car can accommodate for all scenarios. It looks sharp on the outside and has one of the highest quality interiors in the executive car class.

The Virtual Cockpit remains probably the best digital set-up on sale. The new, higher-resolution setup is still ruthlessly easy to master, with every control at your fingertips, right on the steering wheel. The A4’s interior remains high-brow, and there’s good space front and rear.

This car ticks most boxes, an all-rounder!

Title: 2018 Ford Transit Custom 300 Crew Cab Limited
Description:
First registered – 28/03/2018

Fords are always an incredibly popular van, especially  in the crew cab.
Mainly down to the appealing looks, reliability and good residual values.
This particular one comes with some additional cosmetic upgrades such as different wheels, extended body coloured from splitter and black side rails.

Only covered 34,000 miles. this van is in very good condition.
Comes with reversing camera, heated front seats, sat nav and bluetooth

The Crew Cab has a spacious interior that can comfortably accommodate up to 6 passengers, including the driver.

The cargo area is located behind the rear seats and can hold up to 6.8 cubic meters of cargo.

Vehicle has just had a full service with discs and pads replaced also.

Cosmetically and mechanically fantastic.

Title: Mercedes A45 AMG 4MATIC 7 Speed (376bhp) Dynamic Package
Description:
First Registered on 01/09/2016

This car comes with almost every conceivable option, other than the Aero pack i don’t think there was a box that wasn’t ticked.

Although i do love the Aero pack, we have had several without it, and i do think without it it ads to “Wolf in sheeps clothing” affect.

The bright silver outside is very nicely broken up with the black sliding panoramic sunroof, along with the gloss black trims. The night pack, which gives black mirror caps, rear privacy and matt black wheels help entice the looks.

The beautiful styling carries on inside. The seats are just delightful. Full black leather sports seats, they hold you in place perfectly and are electrically adjustable so you can get yourself in the perfect position at the push of a few buttons on the door card. In your hands is this flat-bottomed half leather and Alcantara multifunctional steering wheel with aluminium spokes and the “AMG” logo that looks and feels fantastic.

Of course, there’s an infotainment screen and it’s controlled by the small scroll wheel behind your gear selector. It has everything you’d expect; SatNav, Reversing camera,Bluetooth Media, Radio and vehicle settings, but it also has an awesome set of dials that give you live reading of how much horsepower you’re producing, your oil temperature and your engine temperature. The whole interior consists of only the highest materials and builds quality.

What’s not to love about a hatchback with a 2.0 turbocharged engine, 4-wheel drive, 376hp and an absolutely incredible dual-clutch gearbox? The car drives so effortlessly when in comfort mode but, having the Rare Drivers Dynamic pack, there are 4  more fun modes to choose from; sport, sport plus, individual and…the optional race giving you LSD and harder damper settings. In comfort, the steering is light, the throttle is easy and it’s a real pleasure to drive. The individual mode lets you customize each setting to suit your drive so you can easily switch between a set mode and your personal one. Each mode alters the steering, suspension and customises the ESP and transmission evidently turning the car more and more into an absolute demon on the track.

The looks, the features, the noise and the ridiculously performance – It’s got it all!

Reverse Camera with Guidance lines, Heated seats, Sports exhaust, Dual-Zone Climate Control, Front and Rear Heated Screen, LED AMG Side Sills, Red Brake Callipers, Electric Windows and Push to Start.

Title: 2014 VW Transporter 2.0TDI  Crewbcab
Description:
First registered – 05-09-14

The VW Transporter T5.1! This iconic van has been a mainstay of the commercial and private vehicle market for years, and this version adds a touch of sporty flair to the mix. So, let’s take a closer look.

This comes with 6 Leather wrapped seats and a full Sportline kit which includes day running lights.

Black 20″ alloy wheels, Pioneer Touchscreen  Head Unit with Bluetooth Audio along with Sat Nav, reversing camera and sensors.

Insulated in the rear along with Alcantara Headlining for that luxury finish.

Beyond the Bulkhead in the rear is again another compartment that’s fully carpeted and insulated, in there you will also find an Inverter with a leisure battery along with a smart TV.

This would make a perfect day van.

This Van really looks the part with its sleek, blacked-out front grille, 20-inch alloy wheels, and lowered suspension. Along with a unique body kit and a great colour, this is a great buy.

Overall, this is an excellent van that looks great and is a joy to drive. It’s practical and comfortable, with plenty of space for passengers and cargo.  If you’re in the market for a van, this one is definitely worth considering.

Title: 2019 Ford Transit Custom 280 Ltd
Description:
First registered 28-06-2019

The Ford Transit Custom Limited is a mid-size commercial van that offers a range of features and capabilities for businesses and individuals who need to transport cargo or passengers. Here are some highlights of the vehicle:

Performance: The Transit Custom Limited comes with a 2.0-litre EcoBlue diesel engine that produces 168 horsepower and 298 lb-ft of torque. It is paired with a six-speed manual  transmission that provides smooth and efficient shifting.

Cargo Capacity: The cargo area has a maximum payload capacity of 1,480 pounds and a maximum cargo volume of 202.8 cubic feet. The van also has a low-load floor, which makes it easier to load and unload cargo.

Safety Features: The 2019 Transit Custom Limited comes with a range of safety features, including a rearview camera, lane departure warning, pre-collision assist with automatic emergency braking and more.

Technology: The van also comes with a range of technology features, including an infotainment system with a touchscreen display, Bluetooth connectivity, and a USB port. Also offered are advanced features such as navigation, a rearview camera, and a Wi-Fi hotspot.

Overall, the 2019 Ford Transit Custom Limited is a practical and capable commercial van that offers a range of features and capabilities. It is a good choice for businesses and individuals who need a reliable and versatile vehicle for transporting cargo or passengers.

This van has been previously been fitted with racking in the back that can easily be removed if not needed.

Title: 2016 Audi TT COUPE 2.0T FSI S Line S Tronic
Model: TT COUPE 2.0T FSI S Line S Tronic
Description:
First Registered – 12/03/2016

Under the Bonnet we have the rapid 2 litreS tonic  230 bhp engine which produces 280 ft-lb of torque, 0-62 in just 5.2 seconds. The TT has become as much a technological flagship for Audi as the A8, with features like the Virtual Cockpit installed here before anywhere else. Drive Select is standard across all models, with four modes covering Auto, Comfort, Efficiency and Dynamic. Progressive Steering has been introduced , a variable steering ratio that is designed to make life easier when parking. The Audi TT is fast and fun to drive and it really does know how to put a smile on your face. The front-wheel drive Audi TT is now featuring a clever electronic differential designed to improve cornering speeds and much better handling on them windy B roads or even on the track.

The S line Trim level on the Exterior adds shiny silver 20-inch alloy wheels ,electronic spoiler, a more aggressive body kit and special all-weather LED headlights, which adapt by extinguishing bulbs to prevent dazzling oncoming traffic.

Inside the Audi TT S-line the cabin really is the real highlight it comes with body hugging fully heated S-Line sports seats , Bluetooth connectivity, DAB radio , half leather half alcantara seats, ISOFIX child seat mounts, aircon sat nav , parking sensors and the incredible Bang & Olufsen stereo system. The dashboard has been vastly simplified on the new TT, with no central screen or confusing buttons. Instead, everything has been housed within the driver’s instrument binnacle, replacing the conventional dials with a 12.3-inch Virtual Cockpit display which really is incredible. Owners can customise the screen depending on their needs, with Audi’s MMI interface allowing control of the car’s sat-nav, stereo and telephone, as well as display of the usual speedo and rev counter setup. It’s really intuitive to use, and brings a new dimension to the mainstream car interior. Quality is top notch, with plenty of high-grade leather and soft-touch plastics. The steering wheel is a flat bottom multi-function steering wheel which allows you to control the radio and also phone calls without having to take the hands off the wheel. While as you’d expect in a TT, material quality is superb throughout, with tactile and beautifully executed switchgear. Circular air vents integrating the control function and display for the air-conditioning are another highlight. The central trio feature the temperature, airflow and fan speed control, while the outer pair by the doors have the control for the heated seats. This really is a beautifully designed cockpit.

Title: 2012 Volkswagen Golf, 2.0 TSI (270ps) R Hatchback 5DR
Description:
Registered on the 15/06/2011.
Here’s a special one for you. 270ps, 4-wheel-drive, 6 speed manual and 5 doors!
The MK6 Volkswagen Golf R. How good does this car look?! The Gloss white with silver Talladega alloy wheels is a simple yet very classy stance, colour coded mirror caps, twin centrally located exhaust tailpipes that protrude from a rear diffuser and the gloss black front grilles – Both front and rear lights are super unique and have an evil look as well as being substantially efficient at lighting up the road ahead!
The interior is just as special as the exterior. This one is fitted with the full leather Recaro heated seats, You’ll also find a set of rubber topped aluminium sports pedals and a multifunctional leather-wrapped steering wheel with the “R” logo on the centre spoke. The centre console is brilliantly laid out. There is a large touchscreen with shortcut buttons either side and it has everything you need such as Sat Nav, Radio, Media, a CD player and Bluetooth telephone connection. Below that screen are all of your climate controls options and your heated seat buttons! Your reversing Camera also shows up on the screen when you put the car into reverse. It’s very decluttered and easy to quickly find what you want or need.
Practicality is something that Golf’s are known for and the R is no exception. 5 doors, a large boot and plenty enough leg room in the rear seats.
Now, the drive. As I said before, 270ps, 258lb ft, 4-wheel-drive and one amazing gearbox. The Haldex 4-wheel-drive system is incredibly clever as it sends power to each individual wheel and, more importantly, it sends power to the wheels with the most grip, keeping to planted to the ground through the corners! This car is fitted with the optional ACC switchable adaptive dampers so you have three suspension settings; Comfort, normal and sport. Each gets more aggressive than the previous.
Electric Windows, Heated Mirrors, Adaptive Headlights, 4-Wheel ABS, AUX, USB, Electric Folding Mirrors and Cruise Control

Title: 2017 Ford Focus ST3 Estate 2.0 EcoBoost
Description:
First registered – 05/07/2017

Most estate cars put family-friendly versatility ahead of driving fun, but this thing is different.

The ST-3 estate comes with 18-inch alloys, a bodykit and sporty uprated suspension. An 8-inch touchscreen with Bluetooth and navigation along with reversing camera, Leather Recaro sculpted sports seats, automatic headlamps and wipers, climate control and keyless go. In Addition to the ST2 it has Xenon headlamps with washers, red brake callipers, power folding mirrors, parking sensors, cruise control and power-adjustable heated seats.

In this estate format, with a 476-litre boot, it attains a new level of practicality while still looking and driving as well as its five-door sister model.

The ST has extremely sharp and beautifully weighted steering, strong grip and superb body control. Factor in the six-speed manual gearbox’s snappy shift action plus the powerful brakes, and even a short blast down a twisting back road will leave you grinning from ear to ear.

This car has been fitted with the Factory Mountune package.

A really rare car in great condition topped off by a beautiful colour.

Title: Subaru Impreza 2.5 WRX STI Type UK (300bhp) Hatchback
Model: Impreza 2.5 WRX STI Type UK (300bhp) Hatchback
Description:
First registered – 31/03/2010

Subaru Impreza 2.5 WRX STI Type UK (300bhp) Hatchback Finished in Silver with Black wheels.
Driven by a 2.5 litre Flat 4 turbocharged engine, Im sure you can imagine this car is no slouch.
The handling is everything you would expect for an all-wheel-drive car with a pacey engine; Basically, epic levels of grip, even on lousy surfaces. These cars are a whole load of fun and continue to be residually strong.

Good service history with a recent service being done along with 4 new tyres. The interior is dark grey Alcantara with STI logos in red. STI 6 speed close-ratio manual gearbox, comes standard with an SI-Drive Mode system and DCCD centre diff controller. This example is in excellent condition. This car needs to be viewed and driven to be fully appreciated.

This car has had an upgraded Exhaust, so it sounds like a Subaru should.

Title: 2019 KTM 790 Adventure
Description:
The KTM 790 Adventure  is a mid-sized adventure motorcycle that uses the same LC8 799c parallel-twin engine used in the 790 Duke but with a revised mapping. It peaks at 95 hp at 8,000 rpm and 65ft/lb torque at 6,500 rpm which is almost the same as that of the BMW F850GS or the Honda Africa Twin. Being approximately so much lighter than the Honda or BMW though, the KTM definitely feels like a more responsive, nimble, and agile machine. The new KTM 790 Adventure presents an excellent mix of on-road comfort with sporty handling, and off-road capability. Consider it a slightly more pavement-focused version of KTM’s new flagship bike that is the 790 Adventure R model. The KTM 790 is the perfect option for riders wanting to get all the adventure possible out of a motorcycle without being overwhelmed by the size and power of the biggest bikes now in the market.

There’s the visually appealing TFT display in full color that’s quite customizable so riders can decide on which information they want displayed. In addition, the display automatically adjusts depending on lighting conditions. With more basic displays on other adventure bikes, changes from cloud cover or tree canopy to direct sunlight aren’t such a hindrance in a rider’s ability to read the KTM’s display. The display has easy to flip through menu items, making it quick to find the specific information being sought, It also comes with the option of ” KTM’s My Ride” feature that connects with phones, so riders can receive calls hands-free, and follow GPS directions on the bike’s TFT display. The 790 Adventure comes with a large and adjustable windshield to deflect windblasts at high speeds, and its 40mm of vertical adjustability can be taken advantage of in less than 30 seconds, after a few rounds of practice. On the Adventure it comes with an adjustable seat for riders of varying inseams or riding demands. Its simple, two-piece design for rider and passenger is easy to remove and adjust in less than a minute, and offers the right balance of width and firmness for feel and comfort.

The KTM 790 Adventure performs extremely well for on-road conditions, while maintaining considerable prowess in the dirt. With its low center of gravity and low seat height, flipping back and forth in the twisties is easy and fun. The KTM’s 95 hp engine has one of the better power-to-weight ratios in this category, and anyone with a basic understanding of physics knows how this plays out. Good luck getting to sleep the night before, when you know this jumper awaits you in the morning.

Title: 1991 NISSAN FIGARO
Description:
Registered on 01-09-1991

Smoother than a Barry white record and cuter than a basket of puppies!
Here we have a superb, and meticulously maintained Nissan Figaro.
Nissan launched Figaro sales in Japan on Feb. 14, 1991. Limited to 20,000 units, Nissan officials expected demand to outstrip supply. They were right.
It’s remarkably ageless, retaining its bouncy charisma despite being 30 years old.
Best of all, the top folds into the boot.
A 1.0-litre turbocharged four-cylinder engine generates 76 horsepower and 78 pound-feet of torque through a three-speed automatic transmission, a very small, manoeuvrable and easily managed car. If you can’t parallel park the Figaro, you should be walking.
Inside, the white interior and seats are covered in leather with contrasting piping. A special paint is used on top of the dashboard to make it feel soft, while a flat instrument panel places two large chrome-trimmed dials in front of the driver. The left one is the speedometer with smaller inset gauges for fuel and engine temperature; the right a tachometer with a small inset clock.

A roadster that’s stylish, rare and clockwork reliable.
These vehicle are certainly an asset to have, in more ways than one.

These cars are very condition sensitive and this has been priced accordingly.
mechanically and cosmetically in very good order. This will not disappoint any serious buyer.

Title: 2010 Triumph Daytona 675 Tripple
Description:
This a a limited edition and in extremely good condition.

The Triumph Daytona 675 delivers a pure adrenalin rush on road or track. The race-winning three-cylinder engine, with an electrifying blend of midrange drive and screaming top-end power, is perfectly balanced with a precisely calibrated chassis for extreme agility, control and confidence.

An all-aluminum, boomerang-shaped swingarm completes the standing chassis, and comes mounted on an adjustable pivot for an extra layer of ride controlThe front brakes use a radial master cylinder as well as twin radial four-piston calipers and the fully floating 308mm front discs are matched by a 220mm rear. The new wheels are a lightweight five-spoke design and wear super-sticky Pirelli Dragon Super Corsa Pro tyres. Front tyre size is 120/70 ZR17 while the rear is 180/55 ZR17. The Daytona 675 a claimed 123bhp, 12,500rpm with 72Nm torque at 11,750rpm of throaty fun which sounds absolutely incredible when opened up it feels like a racing thoroughbred!. The most impressive thing about the motorcycle is its broad spread of power and excellent fuelling system – a previous failing on some Hinckley sport bikes. The 675 stands alone in the hotly contested sports bike arena and while others might compare it to a myriad of motorcycles, it’s very much a statement of how a pure Triumph sports bike should look and, just as importantly, feel. In one single stroke it has redefined just how a middleweight sports bike should perform, packing as it does a large amount of power and torque into a small, nimble package. The Daytona 675 stands apart immediately with its inimitable, spine-tingling sound and feel. Integral to this is the triple’s inherent advantage of masses of bottom-end torque, linked to a heavy mid-range punch that’s topped with a searing burst of peak power.
Colour: Pearly white fairings with factory blue Frame.

Here we have an absolutely beautiful example of a Japanese imported Nissan Cube.
3rd Generation facelift
These were produced predominately in Japan with a very small European market opening.
Very rare to be seen anywhere outside of Japan.
The Cube is designed as a subcompact vehicle.
It's a little bit bigger than the likes of a Nissan Micra to allow for more comfort and practicality, offering more boot space and better access.
This fantastic little car comes with 5 very comfortable seats perfect for a small young family or even someone who wants a compact economical car that will literally fit anywhere.
From driving the lovely vehicle myself I have found the front seats to be like sitting in a huge comfortable armchair. Such a great place to be for driving in absolute comfort.
Been very well looked after inside and out.
Comes in the beautiful Metallic Black Obsidian paint.
The vehicle drives and handles beautifully.
The vehicle is great for the Manx roads, it's small and nippy cheap to run and fits in anywhere, perfect for our tight roads
The vehicle comes rust free underneath and on the bodywork as can be seen from the fantastic photos.

Please have a good look through all of the pictures to get a true perspective as to how fantastic and clean an example this car truly is.

What more can you ask for?

We are also more than happy to show you through every part of the vehicle.

Features: Manx Car Store are proud to present this Lamborghini Urus V8, This beautiful Urus is a one owner car and has been maintained to the highest standards with full Lamborghini service History. The Lamborghini Urus feels athletic from behind the wheel, steering is quick, and high-speed cornering is stable. The engine powering this joy-filled Urus is a Twin-Turbo 4.0-Liter V8, making a healthy 641 horsepower. This reaches a top speed of 190mph and a 0-60 time of only 3.6 Seconds. Features:
Ford Escort RS Cosworth – The Greatest Ford Escort of All

Ford Escort RS Cosworth Lux Model 4X4 2 owners finished in Imperial Blue. Fully maintained by Noris Motorsport in the UK. A True Fast Ford Unicorn it is simply the highest specification and most technologically advanced of all the Cosworth Rally Cars. It is the combination of distinctive styling with true rally bred innovation which gives this Escort Cosworth its special flair. From the front contoured air dam, body coloured bumper and louvred hood top air intakes to the body colour rocker moulding front fenders with air extraction grilles and Rondell alloy wheels, this is unmistakeably a car built to perform. The tough world of rallying is a convincing proving ground for this 2.0 DOHC 16v turbocharged Cosworth Engine, it guarantees breath-taking performance with sparkling immediate engine response.

Few cars look this good. Fewer still offer such rewards on the open road.

Title: 2003 VAUXHALL VX220 TURBO
Description:
Now this really is a special piece of kit - Based on the early Lotus Elise, the VX220 has all the heritage and dynamics of a fantastic handling roadster, and arguably even better styling to match! 

From factory the VX220 comes with 200BHP and a weight of 920KG - but this example has been tastefully modified to produce a reliable 273BHP to make this little pocket rocket unbelievably quick. 
But it doesn't stop there! It also has full Nitron suspension, a full Miltek exhaust system, a removable hard top, a cloth soft top, rear diffuser, Team Dynamic alloys with sticky Toyo R888 tyres as well as the original wheels and tyres for the car.

This is not a car to be missed - the power, grip, noise and looks really do make it stand out!
