Title: 2016 BMW 435d xDrive M-Sport Gran Coupe 5Dr Auto
Description:
SkillanNaylor Car Company are pleased to offer this 2016 BMW 435d xDrive M-Sport Gran Coupe 5Dr Auto seen in BMW Individual Champagne Quartz Metallic with Oyster Dakota Leather.

Back in 2013 BMW had a rethink regarding the badging structure of their cars. Going forward sporty cars would be even numbers and standard cars would be odd numbers. For example 2, 4, 6 & 8 Series Coupe's, Convertibles and Gran Coupe's. 1, 3, 5 & 7 Series, Hatchback's, Saloon's and Touring's.

The BMW 4 Series range is based upon the platform and underpinnings of the 3 Series range. Before the badge restructuring these cars would of been referred to as 3 Series Coupes & Convertibles. The 4 Series models gained their own identity and style but borrowed chassis parts, running gear and interior from the 3 Series. All three 4 Series models are the same length and width which is slightly larger than the 3 Series in all dimensions.

Of the three body styles available the Gran Coupe is the most popular. It combines the sleek looks of a coupe with the practicality of 4-Doors and crucially a hatchback opening boot. These means that both passengers and luggage can be loaded with ease.

This BMW 4 Series Gran Coupe is coded named F36. When this model was produced it was topped by this model which is the 435d xDrive M-Sport. 435 refers to the engine which is a 3.0L 6-Cylinder Twin Turbo Diesel that develops 313 BHP and 630 Nm torque. The engine is connected to the xDrive 4-Wheel Drive System. This model is an M -Sport model which means that the body styling and chassis setup all have influence from BMW's M division. This combination of power, torque and 4-Wheel drive will get this car from 0-62 MPH in just 4.8 Secs. To put this in to context the BMW E92 M3 with its 4.0L V8 engine takes 4.4 Secs. All this performance whilst achieving 49 MPG (manufacture claimed combined figure) and with an annual IoM road tax cost of just £213. Cake and eat it anyone!

The BMW 435d xDrive M-Sport Gran Coupe is quite a subtle car. It doesn't shout too loud about its performance capabilities. This type of 'under the radar' driving suits the mature character of this car.

BMW like most German car manufactures offer their range of cars in Black, Grey, Silver, White and Blue. If you search the classifieds for this type of car these are the colours you usually get to choose from. If you want something different it is available and BMW call this their Individual program. You can choose from a more diverse range of colours at an additional cost. This car is finished in BMW Individual Champagne Quartz Metallic. The exterior colour contrasts beautifully with the Oyster Dakota Leather upholstery.

This car is presented in excellent condition throughout and with a low mileage of just 25,705 miles.

To summaries the BMW 435d xDrive M-Sport is all the car you will ever need. Its fast, frugal, stylish, practical and capable in all road conditions.

Title: 2018 Fiat 124 Spider 1.4 Multiair Lusso Plus 2Dr Convertible

SkillanNaylor Car Company are pleased to offer this 2018 Fiat 124 Spider 1.4 Multiair Lusso Plus 2Dr Convertible seen in Bossa Nova White with Black Leather upholstery.

Engine Performance: The heart of this convertible masterpiece lies in its 1.4 Multiair turbocharged engine, delivering an impressive 140 horsepower. The power is in your hands as you navigate the open road with ease and experience the true joy of driving.

Title: 2012 Morgan 3-Wheeler
Description:
SkillanNaylor Car Company are pleased to offer this 2012 Morgan 3-Wheeler seen in Teal with Black Leather upholstery.

Introducing the Iconic Morgan 3 Wheeler: A Timeless Masterpiece of Automotive Excellence!

Are you ready to experience the thrill of a bygone era, where the wind in your hair and the rumble of a powerful engine were all you needed for an unforgettable driving adventure? Look no further than the legendary Morgan 3 Wheeler, a true automotive icon that combines classic design, exhilarating performance, and an unmatched sense of freedom.

Unmistakable Design

Step back in time and embrace the timeless charm of the  Morgan 3 Wheeler. With its retro-inspired design, this three-wheeled marvel captures the essence of the golden age of motoring. Its handcrafted body, featuring a sleek and aerodynamic shape, exudes elegance and sophistication. The exposed engine, open cockpit, and unique styling cues pay homage to the vintage racers of yesteryear, making it an absolute head-turner wherever you go.

Exceptional Performance

Underneath its vintage exterior lies a modern heart that beats with exhilarating performance. Powered by a robust 2.0-liter V-twin engine that can trace its heritage back to Harley-Davidson, the Morgan 3 Wheeler delivers an adrenaline-pumping driving experience. This car features a stage one upgrade which lifts the power to approximately 90 horsepower and 103 pound-feet of torque, this lightweight beauty sprints from 0 to 60 mph in just 4.5 seconds, offering an instant rush of speed. The thrilling sound of the engine combined with the engaging manual transmission ensures every drive is an unforgettable experience.

Pure Driving Pleasure

Prepare to be immersed in a driving experience like no other. The Morgan 3 Wheeler features a unique "centre driver" position, allowing you to feel at one with the road. The responsive steering and tight handling enable you to navigate corners with precision and confidence, while the low centre of gravity ensures exceptional stability. The absence of doors and a roof enhances the connection between you and the environment, providing an unparalleled sense of freedom and excitement that is rare in modern-day cars.

Craftsmanship and Attention to Detail

Morgan Motor Company has been synonymous with handcrafted excellence for over a century, and the 2012 Morgan 3 Wheeler is no exception. Meticulously constructed using traditional methods, each vehicle is a work of art, showcasing the skill and dedication of the craftsmen who built it. From the luxurious leather seats to the polished wood trim, every detail is carefully crafted to perfection, creating a cabin that exudes timeless elegance and sophistication. This car has covered just 13,631 miles and is complimented by a full service history with all of the work being carried out by Morgan car specialists.

Modern Comforts

While the 2012 Morgan 3 Wheeler embraces its classic heritage, it also seamlessly integrates modern comforts to enhance your driving experience. The ergonomic seats provide excellent support, ensuring comfort even during long journeys and they are heated so you drive this car all year round. Features such as a full instrument cluster, modern lighting, and great storage features ensure that you can enjoy the nostalgic ride without compromising on convenience or peace of mind.

Become a Part of Automotive History

Owning a Morgan 3 Wheeler means more than just possessing a remarkable vehicle; it means becoming a part of a rich automotive legacy. With only a limited number produced, this rare gem is sure to appreciate in value over time, making it a wise investment for any discerning collector or enthusiast. Whether you choose to display it as a piece of art or take it for exhilarating drives, the Morgan 3 Wheeler is a symbol of automotive passion and will turn heads wherever it goes.

Don't Miss Your Chance

Now is your opportunity to own a true automotive icon. The Morgan 3 Wheeler is waiting for a passionate driver who appreciates the blend of timeless design, exceptional performance, and pure driving pleasure it offers. Don't miss your chance to embark on a journey through time and experience the joy of driving.

Title: 2021 Toyota GR Yaris 1.6 3Dr AWD Circuit Pack
Description:
SkillanNaylor Car Company are pleased to offer this 2021 Toyota GR Yaris 1.6 3Dr AWD Circuit Pack seen in Precious Black Metallic with GR Ultrasuede upholstery.

Introducing the 2021 Toyota GR Yaris Circuit Pack: Unleash the Rally Beast!

Are you ready to experience the ultimate thrill of driving? Look no further than the 2021 Toyota GR Yaris Circuit Pack. This exceptional performance machine has been designed to dominate the rally circuits, delivering heart-pounding speed and agility that will leave you breathless.

Performance like No Other: Under the hood, the GR Yaris Circuit Pack houses a turbocharged 1.6-liter inline-three engine that produces a mind-blowing 257 horsepower and 266 lb-ft of torque. With its lightweight construction and all-wheel drive system, this beast rockets from 0 to 60 mph in a mere 5.5 seconds. The exhilaration of the GR Yaris Circuit Pack's powertrain is unparalleled, making every drive a truly memorable experience.

Rally-Ready Design: Inspired by the legendary World Rally Championship heritage, the GR Yaris Circuit Pack features a striking and aggressive exterior. The aerodynamic lines, enlarged air intakes, and rear spoiler are not only visually appealing but also optimize the car's performance, providing enhanced stability at high speeds. The exclusive Circuit Pack variant is distinguished by its bold Circuit Edition badge, announcing to the world that this car is built for the track.

Unparalleled Handling: Precision is at the heart of the GR Yaris Circuit Pack's design. Its rally-tuned suspension, lightweight forged alloy wheels, and performance tires work in harmony to deliver exceptional handling, allowing you to tackle corners with confidence and maintain control in any situation. The GR-Four all-wheel drive system ensures power is distributed seamlessly for maximum grip and acceleration, giving you an unrivalled level of confidence and control on both the track and the road.

Luxurious and Sporty Interior: Step inside the GR Yaris Circuit Pack and you'll be greeted by a driver-focused cockpit that blends comfort and sportiness. The premium sports seats hug your body, providing excellent support during spirited driving. The leather-wrapped steering wheel, aluminium pedals, and carbon fibre accents add a touch of sophistication, while the advanced infotainment system keeps you connected and entertained throughout your journey.

Cutting-Edge Technology: Toyota's commitment to innovation is evident in the GR Yaris Circuit Pack. Packed with advanced technologies, it features a high-resolution digital instrument cluster that provides real-time performance data, keeping you informed of crucial metrics while you push the limits. The intuitive touchscreen infotainment system offers seamless smartphone integration, so you can access your favourite apps, music, and navigation with ease.

Uncompromising Safety: Your safety is Toyota's top priority, and the GR Yaris Circuit Pack is equipped with a comprehensive suite of advanced safety features. From the robust chassis construction to the advanced driver assistance systems, including adaptive cruise control, lane departure warning, and automatic emergency braking, you can drive with confidence, knowing that Toyota has your back.

The 2021 Toyota GR Yaris Circuit Pack is not just a car; it's a rally machine designed to awaken your inner driver. Whether you're tearing up the racetrack or navigating the urban jungle, this extraordinary vehicle will redefine your driving experience. Don't miss your chance to own this limited-production masterpiece and experience the thrill of a lifetime.

Title: 2021 Audi RS Q3 2.5 TFSI Quattro Vorsprung 5Dr S Tronic Auto
Model: RS Q3 2.5 TFSI Quattro Vorsprung 5Dr S Tronic Auto
Description:
SkillanNaylor Car Company are pleased to offer this 2021 Audi RS Q3 2.5 TFSI Quattro Vorsprung 5Dr S Tronic Auto seen Daytona Grey Pearl Effect with Black/Red Fine Nappa Leather with Red Honeycomb Stitching.

The Audi RS Q3 is their offering in the Super-sport small-medium sized SUV category. It quite a niche category and really only consists of one other car and that is the Mercedes GLA 45 AMG S. Both the RS Q3 and GLA are 400 BHP compact SUV's that are more focused towards on road handling rather than being driven off-road. The RS Q3 does have one USP that stands it above the GLA 45 AMG and that is its engine.

In the GLA you get a 2.0L 4-Clyinder Twin Turbo petrol engine that actually eclipses the RS Q3 for BHP at 416. In the RS Q3 you get a 2.5L 5-Cylinder Turbo petrol engine that develops 400 BHP. However its the noise and response you get from the Audi that totally dominates the car. The off-beat growl of the Audi 5-Cylinder engine harks back to Audi's glory days of rallying in the Group B era. The 5-Cylinder RS engine is also only used in the RS3, TT RS and RS Q3 unlike the Mercedes engine which is used in a number of cars from the A45 up to the C63 AMG. The mighty engine in the RS Q3 is connected to Audis legendary Quattro -4-Wheel Drive system. This gives the car immense grip and handling and limited all-terrain ability. The combination of power & traction will get this car from 0-62 MPH in just 4.5 Secs and on to a limited top speed of 155 MPH.

Audi offers the RS Q3 in three different trim levels from standard to Sport Edition and on to this car the range topping Vorsrung. Vorsrung is best translated in to 'head start'. This car definitely gives you a head start in terms of factory fitted options. A Bang & Olufsen Surround Sound Stereo, Adaptive LED Headlights, Heated/Electric Front Seats, Apple Car Play and 21" Alloy Wheels are all part of the specification of this car.

This Audi RS Q3 is able to mix maximum sportiness with luxury and quality very easily. The overall fit and finish are first class from the deep pearl effect Daytona Grey paintwork to the fine Nappa Black Leather upholstery. The panel gaps are super tight and the the interior plastics are of a lovely soft touch type. The cabin space is very generous and will easily accommodate 5 adults and the boot will swallow all of their luggage.

This car is presented in immaculate condition throughout and with just 11,681 miles. If you are in the market for a super powerful, characterful, luxury compact SUV that is also very practical look no further.

Title: 2018 Volkswagen Tiguan 2.0 TSI 180 4Motion R-Line 5Dr DSG Auto
Description:
SkillanNaylor Car Company 2018 Volkswagen Tiguan 2.0 TSI 180 4Motion R-Line 5Dr DSG Auto seen in Deep Black Pearl Metallic with Black Vienna Leather upholstery.

The Volkswagen Tiguan is a hard car to define. Its probable rivals would be the BMW X1, Mercedes GLA and Audi Q3 however its a larger car than all three. You could then say that it should be pitched at the next category up i.e. the BMW X3, Mercedes GLC or Audi Q5 however it undercuts all three on price. By being both larger than its main rivals and less expensive makes the Volkswagen Tiguan very good value.

The VW Tiguan was first launched in 2007 and was based upon the mark 5 VW Golf architecture. It offered an elevated driving position thanks to its increased ride height. It was available with both petrol and diesel engines and 4-wheel drive or in VW speak 4Motion was offered on some models.

The generation one Tiguan stayed in production until 2016 when it was replaced by this car which is a generation 2. Although there are some Golf elements present in the Tiguan the gen 2 car is actually now based on a different, slightly bigger platform which is why it now offers more space over its direct rivals.

In 2016 the UK government was still banging the drum for diesel powered cars as at the time they were thought to be better for the environment due to their lower C02 output. This car bucks the  trend by being a petrol powered car. If you look on Autotrader and compare the availability of petrol to diesel VW Tiguan's you will see that petrol cars from the 2016-2019 era are much rarer. This makes this car much better suited to island driving thanks to the lack of a DPF (Diesel Particulate Filter) that can block if driven on continued short journeys.

This VW Tiguan is powered by a 2.0L 4-Cylinder Turbo Petrol engine that develops 180 BHP. This gives the car decent performance and acceptable economy. The engine is connected to a 7-Speed DSG Auto Gearbox. A gearbox of this type uses two clutches to change the gears. This is a benefit because one clutch does the odd numbers i.e. 1-3-5-7 and the other clutch does the even numbers 2-4-6. This means that when the car changes gear the next gear is already selected by the second clutch meaning the gear change is very smooth and quick. This car is also a 4Motion (4-Wheel drive) model that features individual selectable driving and terrain modes giving this car genuine all-terrain ability.

The VW Tiguan is offered in a variety of trim levels from S, SE, Match and like this car R-Line. R-Line gives you a more defined body styling kit, larger bi-colour Alloy Wheels and R-Line branded sports front seats.

Like all German cars the factory options list available for this car is quite extensive. This car benefits from having the interior upgraded to full black Vienna leather and with a Panoramic Glass Sunroof. This car also has heated front seats, side steps and privacy glass to name just a few of the features on this car.

Offered in excellent condition throughout and with just 40,613 miles which is backed up by a full service history. This car looks very moody thanks to its all-black colour combo which is highlighted by the silver roof bars and side steps.

In conclusion if you are looking for a spacious SUV that looks as good as it drives look no further.

Title: 2008 Porsche 997 Carrera 2 3.6 Coupe
Description:
SkillanNaylor Car Company are pleased to offer this 2008 Porsche 997 Carrera 2 3.6 Coupe seen in Atlas Grey Metallic with Black Leather upholstery.

Modern Classic cars have become a firm favourite with SkillanNaylor Car Company. A modern classic is best described as a car that has attained cult or classic status quite early on in its life. Its a car that has a modern feel but is devoid of the latest technology. A car that can been driven everyday or kept for those special occasion drives. A modern classis car should offer a rewarding and analogy driving experience that is an event to drive every time you get behind the steering wheel. This 2008 Porsche 997 Carrera 2 3.6 Coupe ticks everyone of the modern classic boxes.

This car looks stunning thanks to its factory fitted Aerokit Cup body work and 19" Turbo style alloy wheels that both give this car a GT3 style. It features a very traditional 3.6L Boxer Flat-6 petrol engine connected to a 6-Speed manual gearbox. It sounds great thanks to the factory fitted sports exhaust and it has just 30,325 miles which is backed up by an extensive service history.

Although now 15 years old this car still has a modern feel. It does have PCM -Navigation however there are limitations with this sort of tech at this age. The ride quality is on the sporty side but perfectly capable as a daily driver. The Porsche 911 is true sports car however this does not mean its impractical. You do get 4 x seats however the back seats are best left for children and thanks to the rear engine layout you get a very deep and specious area in the front of the car for luggage.

Like almost any Porsche this car is an event to drive. It makes you feel special and you know that the car has been designed to be driven. No one would ever see a car like this as a simple mode of transport to get from A-B. This sort of car is one you would come up with excuses to drive as much as possible.

Porsche have a very healthy owners club here on the Isle of Man and hold regular get togethers and drive outs. This car would be very welcomed by the club and a great way to get involved with the local Porsche and classic car scene.

Title: 2022 Porsche Taycan 4S Cross Turismo 5Dr Auto
Description:
SkillanNaylor Car Company are pleased to offer this 2022 Porsche Taycan 4S Cross Turismo 5Dr Auto see in White with Black Leather upholstery.

In this modern motoring world where you choice of fuel is now petrol, diesel or electric it's sometimes difficult to know which way to go. It can also be difficult for car manufactures to decide what they want their new cars to be able to do. When Porsche developed the Taycan it was very simple. It had to look, feel and drive like a Porsche but be powered be electric.

When you see a Porsche Taycan you instantly know its a Porsche. All of the modern Porsche design queue's are there. Sculptured round wheel arches, large alloy wheels, a low roof line, a wide rear track and an sleek overall body design. The external design of the Taycan looks like a 911 with an extra bit added in to the middle. When you get inside the car the design is equally impressive. Some car manufactures talk about the number of dash screens a car has and were they are placed. In the Taycan the whole dash is a screen. The driver looks at a digital version of the traditional ringed dials you would find in any old school Porsche. The centre part is where the majority of the info is displayed including the Sat-Nav and then in front of the passenger there is further info about the car including the media and radio.

When you get to drive a Porsche Taycan it is fast...like proper fast. In this car 0-62 MPH takes just 4.1 Secs. It has permanent 4-Wheel drive which helps put all of its power down all of the time. Talking of power this car produces what equates to 523 BHP thanks to its twin electric motors. This performance doesn't come at the sacrifice of range though. Fully charged this car has a manufacture stated range of up to 304 miles.

Porsche offers the Taycan in three different levels. Standard, 4S and Turbo with each car getting progressively more power from its electric motors and a higher level of factory equipment. This car is a 4S model

The Taycan is a fantastic car and one of the best in Porsches current line up irrespective of whether its powered by an internal combustion engine or electric. Its ultra modern but it doesn't shout 'i'm an electric car'. If there would be one criticism it would be on practicality. The rear space is not enormous and the boot is not that spacious............Hold on, what you need a Porsche Taycan Cross Turismo.

The Porsche Taycan Cross Turismo is effectively an estate or a more fitting name would be Shooting Brake version of the Taycan. You get more rear passenger space and better head room and a larger boot. This particular cars flexibility is further enhanced by the optional 5-seat configuration.

This car was first registered to its previous owner on September 2022 and it has now covered just 1,500 miles. The manufacture warranty is in place until 2025 and the lead-time for a new order for a car of this type is well over 12 months. If you look at the price for this car there is no doubt it is a large chuck of money however when you compare to other Porsche's it is in line with everything else they sell. It's difficult to offer competitor cars to the Taycan. BMW, Mercedes and Audi offer large electric cars but none will match the overall appeal of the Taycan.

So in summary if your wants & needs list for your next car is quite long and has things on it like, electric, power, performance, good range, handsome good looks, high level of tech, 4-Wheel drive, spacious, practical etc this Porsche Taycan Cross Turismo could be just the car for you.

Title: 2013 Volkswagen Caravelle 2.0 BiTDi BMT Executive 180 4Motion DSG Auto
Model: Caravelle 2.0 BiTDi BMT Executive 180 4Motion DSG Auto
Description:
SkillanNaylor Car Company are pleased to offer this 2013 Volkswagen Caravelle 2.0 BiTDi BMT Executive 180 4Motion DSG Auto seen in Reflex Silver Metallic with Anthracite Alcantara/Leather upholstery.

Versatility - Ability to adapt or be adapted to may different functions or activities.

When you look for your next vehicle some people will have a distinct list of requirements that their new vehicle must have or be able to do. These requirements can be the ability to carry more than 5 people, that there is enough luggage carrying capacity for all of the occupants and that you can adapt the vehicle to carry large items.

If these requirements also state that the vehicle must have a luxury feel, have decent performance and the ability to travel in adverse terrain or weather conditions the list of what you can choose starts to get quite small.

This Volkswagen Caravelle has the art of versatility mastered. It can carry up to 7 people thanks to its 4 x Captains Chairs and bench that will seat 3 x people. All of the seats in the rear of the vehicle can be repositions or removed. This means you can have 4 or 5 seats and a massive boot area or just 2 seats and the back of the vehicle will then match a Volkswagen Transporter van.

This Caravelle is an Executive model which means you get soft Alcantara/Leather upholstery along with heated front seats, twin electric sliding side doors, dual zone climate control and front & rear parking sensors.

The engine on this Caravelle is as 2.0L 4-Cyllinder Twin Turbo Diesel that develops 180 BHP. The engine is connected to a 7-Speed DSG Auto gearbox and on to a 4Motion 4-Wheel Drive system. This gives the vehicle excellent on road handling and limited all-terrain ability.

This Caravelle is 2013 T5 model with just over 90k miles. When a vehicle reaches this age and mileage it is fair to assume it will of had some work carried out on it to maintain its condition. In this car its back story is quite detailed.

The most recent owner bought the car whilst the world was in midst of the Covid lock down. Since then it has had £££££ spent on it.

Title: 2019 BMW 320d M-Sport (Tech) 4Dr Saloon Auto
Description:
SkillanNaylor Car Company are pleased to offer this 2019 BMW 320d M-Sport (Tech) 4Dr Saloon Auto seen in Black Sapphire Metallic with Mocha Vernasca Leather featuring Night Blue contrast stitching.

The BMW 3 Series has always been and still is the core model in their line up of saloon cars. It has now been on sale for over 48 years and gone through 7 different versions. Each improving on the last with more powerful and efficient engines, higher levels of equipment and technology and improved safety and crash protection.

This car is the latest mark seven version referred to as a G20 which was designed by Alexey Kezha. This version of the BMW 3 Series is based upon the Cluster Architecture (CLAR) platform. This platform is a modular design and is used on a wide variety of other BMW cars such as the X6, Z4 and i4. The chassis is a mix of high strength Steel and Aluminium. This makes the car both strong and light which improves the overall feel and handling of the car.

The obvious main rivals to the BMW 3 Series would be the Audi A4 and Mercedes C Class. If you drive any of these cars you will not be disappointed. All offer a premium well built cabin with great ergonomics and a wide range of engine, gearbox and chassis options. I would always sway towards BMW is i feel they offer the most sporting driving experience. After all they do build 'The Ultimate Driving Machines'.

This BMW 3 Series is a 320d which means it is powered by a 2.0L 4-Cylinder Turbo Diesel engine that develops 184 BHP and crucially just 112 g/Km C02. This means you get good performance and economy paired with an annual Isle of Man road tax cost of just £71.

BMW offer a variety of trim levels in all of their cars. These are usually referred to as SE, Sport, X Line, Luxury and M-Sport. This BMW 3 Series is an M-Sport model which means you get body styling and chassis set up that is influenced by BMW's M division. You get a very pretty set of 18" Multi-spoke alloy wheels, a lower more aggressive body styling kit, lower stiffer suspension and a cabin that features sports seats and a sports steering wheel.

When anyone looks at purchasing a car from a premium car manufacture they expect the vehicle specification to be extensive and impressive. Thankfully with this car you will not be disappointed. It features the Tech Pack which includes Head-Up display which projects info about the car directly in front of the driver on to the windscreen. You also get a powered bootlid, keyless entry & start, Harman Karadon Stereo, reversing assist camera and LED headlights to name just a few of the features and options fitted to this car.

Another aspect that should be important to any car buyer is the provenance of the vehicle. This is a one owner, locally supplied car with full BMW service history and just 12,878 miles. It is presented in immaculate condition with both keys and a full compliment of hand books present.

In summary if you are looking for a great spec, low mileage car that won't break the bank to run or own look no further.

Title: 2009 Audi R8 V10 5.2 Quattro Coupe
Description:
SkillanNaylor Car Company are pleased to offer this 2009 Audi R8 V10 5.2 Quattro Coupe seen in Phantom Black Pearl with Extended Fine Black Nappa Leather upholstery.

If you focus on the three big German car manufactures e.g. BMW, Audi and Mercedes they are always playing car leap frog. One will launch a new car and then another will launch something soon after that is a bit more powerful and a bit faster. Sometimes however one of them will surprise you.

Most high performance German cars are based around 4Dr saloon or 2Dr coupe body styles. In 2006 the car that lead BMW in the BHP arms race was the BMW M6 Coupe. This was a front engined, 2Dr coupe powered by a 5.0L V10 Engine that developed 507 BHP. It had genuine technology that BMW had learnt during their years at Formula 1 and would get from 0-62 MPH in under 4 Secs.

Mercedes fought this with the Mercedes SL65 AMG Coupe. This car had 6.0L V12 Twin Turbo engine that developed 604 BHP. Mercedes were and still are the automotive partner for F1 and a version of the SL was used as the Pace Car for most F1 races. It was driven by the legendary driver Bernd Mayländer.

As both of these cars are front engined, rear wheel drive, 2Dr coupes you would of expected Audi to launch something similar to meet the other manufactures head on. Wrong!

To combat the BMW M6 and Mercedes SL Audi launched the R8. This was a mid engined, 4-Wheel Drive 2Dr Coupe that looked more like a rival to something from either Ferrari or Lamborghini. That's right Audi was now in the Supercar business.

The R8 was available with two engine options. The first was a 4.2L V8 which was borrowed from the Audi RS4. This was a great engine that developed 414 BHP. On its own this was a great car but with under 500 BHP it wasn't a true Supercar. Audi remedied this when they introduced the 5.2L v10 version of the R8. This developed 525 BHP and shares a lot of its architecture with the engine found in the Lamborghini Gallardo. The VAG group were now the owners of Lamborghini and the R8 and Gallardo were developed together.

At this point in the history of fast cars manufactures were obsessed with drawing on the influence of Formula 1. This meant that F1 derived paddle change gearbox's were all the rage. The Audi R8 was available with such a gearbox and it was referred to as S-Tronic. Most buyers chose the new style gearbox over the traditional 6-Speed gated manual.

The Audi R8 was built in a new factory in Neckkarsulm, Germany and it is construction in mostly Aluminium. Although now 16 years old the design of the R8 still looks fantastic today. Unlike the more obvious designs from the likes of Ferrari, Lamborghini and Porsche the Audi R8 still looks like concept car.

In the modern motoring world where it seams that we are inflicted with the launch of a new electric car on an almost daily basis a car with a 6-Speed manual gearbox and thunderous V10 petrol engine is the perfect antidote.

At £54,995 this car also represents excellent value. £54,995 is a lot of money to spend on a car however what other Supercars that can match the R8 are available for the same money. You won't buy any Lamborghini for this amount of money and a Ferrari would have to be much older and no where near as capable.

Some cars will get you from A to B. Some cars will get you to B much faster than others. Only a few cars like the Audi R8 are an event to drive. They make you feel good and epitomise what it means to be a petrol head and love cars & driving.

This car is presented in fantastic condition throughout and is complimented by a full Audi service history.

Title: 2012 Bentley Continental GT 6.0 W12 Mulliner 2Dr Coupe Auto
Model: Continental GT 6.0 W12 Mulliner 2Dr Coupe Auto
Description:
SkillanNaylor Car Company are pleased to offer this 2012 Bentley Continental GT 6.0 W12 Mulliner 2Dr Coupe Auto seen in Anthracite Grey Metallic with Portland/Ebony Diamond Stitched Leather upholstery.

Bentley historic timeline

  • 1919 - Founded by W O Bentley
  • 1931 - Acquired by Rolls Royce
  • 1980 - Acquired by Vickers
  • 1988 - Acquired by Volkswagen Group

The acquisition of Bentley by VW in 1988 heralded a new era for the brand and the start of whole new range of cars. The large luxury 4-door saloon style was still offered with the Mulsanne but it was the New Continental GT 2Dr Coupe that spiked the most interest.

The Continental GT 2Dr Coupe harked back to original Bentleys from W O Bentley. Sleek body design matched to a powerful engine capable of carrying the occupants on great driving adventures.

Its easy to forget that the Bentley brand was now owned by a company more used to making 5Dr hatchbacks like the Golf. Under VW ownership the Bentley brand now had the investment and support to improve the quality of the cars and introduce new technologies that so far had not been offered by the brand.

This first Continental GT Coupe was launched back in 2003 and stayed in production until 2011 when it was replaced by this car obviously known as the generation two. The idea of traveling great distance at great speed is what the Continental GT Coupe was all about.

The takeover by VW also brought another very exciting element to the Bentley brand and that was the new W12 engine. Bentley's had historically be powered by a 6.75 litre V8 petrol engine. It was a great engine but its origins dated back a long way. The all-New W12 was a 6.0L petrol engine in a W12 configuration that also featured two turbos. This monster of an engine developed 560 HP and 650 Nm torque. The Continental GT Coupe also brought another first to the Bentley brand and that was 4-Wheel Drive. Now you could use all of the power all of the time.

Bentley has always been an exclusive car manufacture. In relation to other car manufactures and the rest of the VW group their sales volumes were tiny. They make very special cars at a price out of reach for most people. When ordering a new Bentley there is vast range of colours and trims to choose from plus lots of features and options. Sometime people want something extra special. This is when Bentleys Mulliner department gets involved.

Mulliner driving specification as its often referred to gives you larger alloy wheels, diamond stitched quilted leather upholstery that is available in a wider choice of colours and a broader selection of interior trims from more exotic woods to turned aluminium. This car features 21" Mullier Alloy wheels painted in Anthracite grey, Portland (cream) primary hide (leather) with Ebony (black) secondary hide. The dash and door casings have dark Walnut veneer trim and the four seat headrests are embroidered with the Bentley logo. This configuration gives this car an understated yet opulent luxury feel that is very in keeping with what Bentley is all about.

Presented in excellent condition throughout and with just 46,060 miles that is backed up by a complete and full Bentley service record with the last service only completed a short time ago.

The Bentley Continental GT 6.0 W12 Mulliner is a true drivers car. If you want to arrive in style look no further.

Title: 2008 BMW E92 M3 4.0 V8 2Dr Coupe M-DCT Auto
Model: E92 M3 4.0 V8 2Dr Coupe M-DCT Auto
Description:
SkillanNaylor Car Company are pleased to offer this 2008 BMW E92 M3 4.0 V8 2Dr Coupe M-DCT Auto seen in Jet Black with Black Novillo Leather upholstery.

The 4th generation, E92 variant of the BMW M3 is seen by some as the high point in its 36 years of production. The reason for this is the engine.

The E30 M3 kicked things of in 1986 with the S14 2.3L 4-Cylinder NA engine. This grew to 2.5L for the Sport Evolution model. In 1992 BMW launched the E36 variant of the M3 and this featured the S50 3.0L 6-Cylinder NA engine. This again grew in later years to 3.2L.

In 2000 BMW debuted the E46 M3 and this utilised the S54 3.2L 6-Cylinder engine. This engine is seen by many as the best 6-Cylinder engine ever produced by any car manufacture.

in 2007 BMW launched the E92 M3. With this car things go a whole lot more serious. Gone was the raspy 6-Cylinder S54 engine that developed 343 HP to be replaced by the sonorous wail of the legendary S65 4.0 V8 engine that developed 420 HP at a heady 8,300 RPM. Other than the homologation special E46 M3 GTR the E92 was the first and only M3 to fitted with a 4.0L V8 NA engine.

The S65 V8 utilised genuine lessons learnt in Formula 1. It had individual throttle Butterflys per cylinder. This meant that the throttle response was instant. It was also made mostly of Aluminium which meant that even though it had a displacement of around 25% more that the E46 S54 it weighed almost the same.

The motoring industry journalist at the time instantly fell in love with the E92 M3 and it attracted high praise for everyone that drove it. These are some of the comments from test drivers at the launch event.

"The greatest all-around car in the world", "The finest car on the market, period" and "The best, most complete car in the world".

The engine this E92 M3 is connected to another first for the M3 and that is its 7-Speed M-DCT gearbox. DCT stands for dual clutch transmission. This means that it uses 2 x clutches. One does the even numbers e.g. 2, 4 & 6 and the other does the odd numbers e.g. 1, 3, 5 & 7. This means that when you change gear either automatically or via one of the steering wheel mounted gearshift paddles the next gear is already pre-loaded and the change is instance. Again, this technology is motorsport derived. The gearbox is connected to an Active M Differential which means you can utilise more of the power more of the time.

The E92 M3 also uses a range of different materials for the body panels. The roof is Carbon Fibre, the bonnet is aluminium, and the front wings and boot lid are made from composite plastic. This drops the overall weight and improves the vehicles handling & dynamics.

Cars like the E92 M3 are now referred to as 'modern-classics'. This means that they are seen as classic cars but are modern enough to be driven every day. They can either be a daily driver or a special treat. Whenever you drive one it will be a memorable occasion.

This E92 M3 was first registered in 2008 and was originally supplied by JKC BMW in Northern Ireland. It came over to the Isle of Man in 2010 and has an extensive service history.

Cars like this are now becoming rarer on the roads and consequently their value is on the rise. You will now pay more for a low mileage E92 M3 than you will pay for the later F80 M3. If you are considering a new car that will be a joy to drive but will also not cost, you the earth in depreciation look no further.

Presented in Jet Black with matching Black Novillo Leather upholstery and only 53,188 miles this car is ready to go.

Title: 2011 Abarth 695 Tributo Ferrari 3Dr Auto
Description:
SkillanNaylor Car Company are pleased to offer this 2011 Abarth 695 Tirbuto Ferrari 3Dr Auto seen in Rosso Corsa with Nero/Rosso Alcantara Cloth upholstery.

The Abarth 695 Tributo Ferrari was built by Abarth in collaboration Ferrari and shares its design and style with Ferrari's from the same period e.g. The Ferrari 430 Scuderia.

Just 500 examples were made available and only 152 in right-hand-drive. This makes the Abarth 695 Tributo Ferrari one of the rarest and most sought after hot hatches made.

When designing this car there was only really one colour to chose for the exterior. This was Rosso Corsa which is of course Ferrari's signature colour. The exterior of the car is further enhanced by the Scuderia racing stripes, 17" Grigio Challenge Alloy Wheels, Carbon Fibre door mirror covers and the all important front wing mount Scuderia Shield badges.

The interior is paired with Nero/Rosso Alcantara Cloth upholstery that features red highlight stitching and Abarth embroidered on to the front seat headrests. The front seats are a work of art and are made of Carbon Fibre by a company called Sabelt.

The rest of the interior is beautifully put together and features predominately Carbon Fibre trim on the dash and black leather with red stitching on the dash pod. There is also Trubito Ferrari brand floor mats and Aluminium accelerator and brake pedals.

The Abarth 695 Tributo Ferrari is powered by a 1.4L 4-Cylinder Turbo T-Jet 180 engine. This power along with a curb weight of just 1,100 Kgs means this car gets to 60 MPH in just 7 Secs. This car also sounds very purposeful thanks to the Record Monza quad exhaust.

To further cement the link with Ferrari the Abarth 695 Tributo Ferrari was only offered with one transmission option. This being an F1 inspired 6-Speed Sports Auto that features steering wheel mounted gear shift paddles.

To go with the Abarth 695 Tributo Ferrari there is a multitude branded merchandise. This includes a tailored car cover, a USB cable, a car care kit and a smart phone holder.

This particular car was supplied new by Lipscomb Cars who are an Abarth main dealer. It has covered just 16,268 miles and is complimented by a full Abarth dealer service history. It is presented in immaculate condition and would make a fine addition to any enthusiasts car  collection.

As of when this vehicle was first listed on our website for sale there were no other Abarth 695 Tributo Ferrari's available for sale in the UK>

Title: 2021 Volkswagen Arteon Shooting Brake 2.0 TSI R 4Motion 5DR DSG Auto
Model: Arteon Shooting Brake 2.0 TSI R 4Motion 5DR DSG Auto
Description:
SkillanNaylor Car Company are pleased to offer this 2021 Volkswagen Arteon Shooting Brake 2.0 TSI R 4Motion 5DR DSG Auto seen Lapiz Premium Blue Metallic with Black/Blue Titanium Leather upholstery.

Its always nice when a car surprises you. When you aren't really aware of a particular model or when you see a car and its much more impressive than you first thought it would be. The Volkswagen Arteon R is just such a car.

From a visual perspective the car which is closest to the Arteon is a Porsche Panamera Sport Turismo as its neither and estate car or hatchback. A Shooting Brake fuses style and practicality together. The Arteon as able to mix a large boot and acres of leg room with a low roof line and a sculptured body. The overall fit and finish would match anything from Audi, BMW or Mercedes and the whole car has a sporty yet luxurious feel.

The Arteon Shooting Brake is a substantial car and measures 4.9M long. This endows it with great leg room for all 5 x passengers and a boot capacity of 565L with the seats up or 1,600L with them down.

The underpinnings of the Arteon are based on VAGs MQB platform and shared with the MK8 VW Golf R. The running gear including the 4Motion 4-Wheel drive are carried over as is the EA888 2.0 4-Cylinder Turbo Petrol engine and 7-Speed Twin-Clutch DSG gearbox. This combination provides the Arteon R with 316 BHP, a 0-62 MPH in just 4.9 Secs and a limited top speed of 155 MPH. This gives the Arteon Shooting Brake R the title as VW's fastest ever estate (type) car. The Arteon R also features a torque vectoring rear axle. This means that up to 50% of the overall power can be sent to the rear wheels and then split across the back axle to aid handling and reduce under steer.

The car has 4 x individual different driving modes, comfort, sport, race and individual. Each alters the dynamic properties of the car in different ways. The Race mode can be activated via a blue R button on the steering wheel which gives you finger tip access to the the most focused set-up available.

As you expect from any car that sits at the top of a manufactures range the features & options on this car are extensive. A Panoramic Glass Sunroof, Electric/Memory/Heated Front Seats, Apple Car Play and 19" Alloy Wheels are all fitted to the Arteon R.

The Arteon Shooting Brake R has only been in production for 18 months so is a rare site on the road. At the time of writing this synopsis there were only 20 similar vehicles available for sale on Autotrader. From a cost perspective the closest rivals to this car would be the likes of an Audi S4 Avant however for this money you would be looking at an older car. You could also go for a VW Golf R Estate however the Golf Estate is nowhere near as stylish as the Arteon plus it has significantly less interior passenger room.

This car is presented in immaculate condition throughout and with just 11,400 miles. It is still covered under its manufacture warranty until 2024 and will come with 12 months road tax included.

In conclusion if you want a stylish, practical, well built car that will be a rare site on the road look no further.

Title: 2021 Peugeot E208 100KW GT 50kWh 5Dr Auto
Description:
SkillanNaylor Car Company are pleased to offer this 2021 Peugeot E208 100KW GT 50kWh 5Dr Auto seen in Pearlescent Vertigo Blue with Anthracite Cloth/Leather upholstery.

The Peugeot E208 is their offering in the increasingly competitive small electric car sector. The big advantage the E208 has over some of its rivals is that it was designed to be an electric from the outset. This means that the batteries are cleverly built in to the floor which improves the overall packaging of the car and the handling due to the lower centre of gravity.

Having driven the car for a few days I have found it to be well built, quiet, nippy, spacious and stylish. The fit and finish are as good as anything else from within this sector i.e. an Electric MINI. The cabin is well insulated which means road noise is kept to a minimum. It feels pretty quick, like hot hatch quick thanks to the instant torque of the electric motor and single speed auto gearbox. Thanks to its 5 door design which again is a bonus compared to the Electric MINI which is only available as a 3-Door i found the car to easily accommodate two adults and two children along with a decent boot. The colour of the car found universal praise from anyone that saw it. It is called Vertigo Blue and it is a pearlescent finish. The body colour contrasts well against the gloss black roof and wheel arches.

Choosing an electric car can to some people which did include myself also mean a lot of faff. Plugging it in, waiting for it to charge, what if it runs out etc. I am happy to say i am converted. The act of plugging-in and charging was very simple.

  • Download the free Pod Point app from the app store.
  • Create an account - Owner, car, payment details
  • Put some funds on your account, i chose £20
  • Find your nearest charger on the app
  • Go to the charger and plug your car in
  • Confirm which charge you haver chose. Each charger has a unique name
  • Press confirm and that is it

The charge finishes once you unplug the car. I had the car on charge for 3 hours which added 100 miles to the total range. This charge cost just £6. As an easy equation that is effectively the same cost as one gallon of petrol so this meant the car could do 100 miles per gallon. No petrol or diesel car can offer this range for this cost.

Taking of range Peugeot state a total range in optimum conditions of 217 miles. If the car was on zero range it would take approximately 7 hours on a 7KW to get to full charge.

The feel of the E208 is of a modern, well thought out car which has all of the 'tech' well integrated in to the design. The easy to use touch screen infotainment system includes Apple Car Play so music streaming and Satellite Navigation are only a finger tip away. I also found the ergonomics to be very good. With the drivers seat set to accommodate someone who is 6ft tall there was still plenty of room in the back for back seat passengers. The steering wheel adjusts for both reach and rake which meant finding your optimum driving position easy.

All in all i found the E208 a great car to live with and to drive. If you are thinking of going electric the Peugeot E208 is definitely worth considering.

Title: 2019 Ford Fiesta 1.5 EcoBoost ST Performance Edition
Description:
SkillanNaylor Car Company are pleased to offer this 2019 Ford Fiesta 1.5 EcoBoost ST Performance Edition seen in Deep Orange with Anthracite Recaro Alcantara/Leather upholstery.

The Ford Fiesta has been in production since 1976 and has always been one of Fords most popular cars. It has consistently been at the top of the new cars sales chart in the UK and is a very common site on our roads.

Over the last 46 years there have been many versions of the Fiesta with each culminating in a powerful sporty range topping model. These have been the XR2, RS1800, RS Turbo and ST models.

The Fiesta is a Mark 8 and is topped by the ST model that is powered by a 1.5L 3-Cylinder Turbo Petrol engine that develops 200 BHP. The Fiesta ST is available in three different variants. These are the ST 1, ST 2 and ST3. Each variant gains more standard equipment but the chassis on each is the same.

In 2019 Ford launched this limited edition of the Fiesta ST called the Performance Edition. There were only 600 produced and all were offered in this stunning colour which is called Deep Orange. This was a Fiesta ST3 turned up to 11. It featured all of the ST 3 options such as Heated Front Seats, Heated Steering Wheel, Reversing Assist Camera, Sat-Nav and Apple Car Play but to name just a few of the features. What is gained over the standard ST was upgrades to the chassis. It now featured a Quaife Limited Slip Differential, lowered & adjustable Coil Over suspension which has been developed at the Nurburging and lightweight 18" Alloy Wheels shod in Michelin Pilot Sport 4 Tyres. The interior is trimmed out in Alcantara/Leather and you are held firmly by the Recaro front seats.

The Ford Fiesta has always had good representation in the Hot Hatch sector and this ST Performance Edition version does not disappoint. Its main rival would be the likes of the MINI JCW hatchback or Polo GTI. Both would come in at a higher price when new and neither would feel as sporty as the Fiesta. Autocar and Evo magazine both gave the Fiesta ST Performance Edition 4.5 starts out of 5 and they both praised it for its lively performance and fine handling.

This local car from new is presented in excellent condition throughout and with just 17,789 miles.

In conclusion if you want the hottest of hot hatchbacks look no further.

Title: 2014 Volkswagen T28 2.0 TDI BlueMotion SWB 4-Birth Camper Van
Model: T28 2.0 TDI BlueMotion SWB 4-Birth Camper Van
Description:
SkillanNaylor Car Company are pleased to offer this 2014 Volkswagen T28 2.0 TDI BlueMotion SWB 4-Birth Camper Van seen in Indium Grey Metallic with Grey Cloth upholstery.

Volkswagen and the term Camper Van have synonymous since the launch of the VW Type 2 way back in 1950. The idea of a relatively small vehicle which could be used for camping captured the minds of people then and it still does today.

One of the main reasons that people like the VW Camper van is that its length is no longer than your average estate car or SUV. This means it will fit on most peoples drives at home or in your average parking space in town. Other, full-size Camper vans require additional parking and are generally more one dimensional than the VW Camper.

This VW Camper van is called a T28 and is based upon the SWB T5 body style. It features a single sliding side door and twin opening barn doors on the back. It is powered by an economical 2.0L 4-Cylinder Turbo Diesel engine mated to a 5-Speed manual gearbox.

The interior is beautifully trimmed out and features a range of units finished in gloss mulberry. The camper is equipped with a twin gas hob, gas oven, sink, and fridge. This Camper is also classed as a 4-birth model as not only can it sleep four people thanks to the rock-n-roll double bed in the cabin and second double bed in the pop top it also has 4 x proper seat belts. This means that mum, dad & the kids can enjoy a weekend out in the country enjoying the Camper lifestyle. This Camper also has a cycle rack attachment which means you can bring your bikes too.

To further aid the 'off-grid' living this Camper can provide it is fitted with a Solar Panel on the roof which is used to power certain features on the vehicle. This means that overnight camping is not restricted to just designated camp sites.

Vehicles like the VW Camper van are made for adventure which can mean long road trips and big miles. This vehicle stands out thanks to its low mileage of just 40,340 miles.

Title: 2021 Toyota GR Yaris 1.6 Circuit Pack by Litchfield
Model: GR Yaris 1.6 Circuit Pack by Litchfield
Description:
SkillanNaylor Car Company are pleased to offer this 2021 Toyota GR Yaris 1.6 Circuit Pack by Litchfield seen in Precious Black Metallic with GR Ultrasuede upholstery.

What does 'homologation' mean? According to google it is the granting of approval by an official authority. Homologation is used in the car industry when a car manufacture builds a car for a particular purpose. In most cases that purpose is for competition i.e. racing or rallying.

If you focus on rallying the epitome of the sport was back in the 1980's in what is known as the 'group B' era. This is when the sport of rallying really pushed the boundaries of was possible. Wild aero kits, massive power and ingenious solutions to problems. It this time and to be able to compete car manufactures only had to make or 'homologate' a small number of cars. This meant that the cars could be wildly more expensive than the road cars they were based upon. Nowadays and due to their rarity these group B based road cars are worth a lot of money. The standout cars from the group B era would be the Audi UR Quattro, Peugeot 205 T16, Lancia Delta S4, MG Metro 6R4 and Ford RS200.

The group B era was only short lived. The monster cars that were used were really too fast for the conditions they were driven in which resulted in multiple crashes and unfortunately a few fatalities to both competitors and spectators.

After the demise of group B the FIA who are the governing body of international motorsport changed the rules around what a manufacture could do to a road car to make it in to a rally car. They now had to make 1,000's of cars if they were going to modify them. This effectively meant the end of the homologation specials. Rally cars now looked very similar to their road car cousins and the sport lost a lot of the drama that had attracted some many spectators to the sport.

If we fast forward to the current World Rally Championship aka WRC the cars again look wild with massive wings and aggressive aero. Until recently power came from a 1.6L Turbo petrol engine and most produced around 300 HP. For the last couple of years the cars have also had some for of electric hybrid assistance. This is supposed to make the cars green however this electrical assistance can also be used for performance. At launch a modern WRC car can have close to 500 HP.

The modern WTRC cars look great but manufactures do not need to make road cars that look the same. A Ford Puma ST looks nothing like its rally car cousin. There is however one car manufacture that does things a little different. Actually very different and that car manufacture is Toyota.

The Toyota GR Yaris was launched at the back end of 2020 after it had been teased for well over 12 months before this. The GR initials stand for Gazoo Racing. They are Toyotas racing department and are responsible for all of Toyotas circuit and rallying programs. They have built F1 cars, Le Mans cars, Touring cars and now rally cars.

The Toyota GR Yaris is as close as you can get to a modern group B car. When you think of a Yaris you think of a small, safe, somewhat boring car driven by people on their way to Bingo. The GR Yaris couldn't be further away from this stereotype. Very little is shared between the standard Yaris and the GR. For starts the GR is a 3-Door body shape. The standard Yaris is only available as a 5-Door. The GR uses a 1.6L 3-Cylinder Turbo Petrol engine. Most other Yaris's are petrol/electric hybrids. Most standard Yaris's are front wheel drive and automatic. The GR has an advanced 4-wheel drive system that is connected to a 6-Speed manual gearbox. The most powerful standard Yaris has 116 BHP. The GR has 257 BHP. The standard Yaris is mostly constructed from steel. The GR has a Carbon Fibre roof skin and Aluminium & composite body panels.

So as you can see the GR Yaris is the closest thing you can get to a rally car for the road. The ultimate fast road car.............or is it? What if you could improve the GR Yaris further. Add more power, stiffen the suspension and focus it even more on being a rallying weapon. Welcome to the Toyota GR Yaris by Litchfield.

Litchfield have been enhancing cars now for over 20 years. They are specialise in improving the performance and handling of cars like the Nissan GTR, BMW M Cars, Audi RS models, Mercedes AMG, Porsche and specific over Japanese cars.

Their upgrade program for the Toyota GR Yaris is quite extensive so a customer can choose from list of items they may want to change or like this car they can choose to have everything that is available.

All of the upgrades are classed as mechanical in that they are physical changes rather than simply increasing the turbo boost pressure. The suspension, wheels, tyres, ECU, exhaust and intercooler are all changed. All of these enhancements add up to a power increase to approximately 350 HP. The total cost for all of the work Litchfield carries out on this GR exceeds £20k. We have all of the relevant invoices & documents covering all of the work.

Although the current state of tune of this car is quite a jump up from standard it is still quite modest in relation to what is possible. The enlarged intercool and SYVECS Engine ECU future proof the car should the new owner want to extract further power from the engine.

Due to the world wide popularity of the GR Yaris it has instantly become a cult classic. No other car manufacture currently offers anything that gets close to it from a performance verses cost perspective. A - B there is not much that will live with a GR. Add in more power, wider wheels & tyres and upgraded suspension and the ability to stay with the GR Yaris by Litchfield gets even harder.

This car was supplied new by us to its one former keep who has covered just 1,716 miles in it. If you grew up watching the group B hero's and now want a piece of the action this is the only car to do it in.

Title: 2013 BMW M3 4.0 V8 Limited Edition 500 2Dr Coupe M-DCT
Model: M3 4.0 V8 Limited Edition 500 2Dr Coupe M-DCT
Description:
SkillanNaylor Car Company are pleased to offer this 2013 BMW M3 4.0 V8 Limited Edition 500 2Dr Coupe M-DCT seen in BMW Individual Stratus Grey Metallic with Black Novillo Leather upholstery featuring blue highlight stitching.

The BMW M3 Limited Edition 500 also known as an LE500 was a runout celebration special edition of the E92 M3 V8. Only 500 were produced and all were offered in a range of stunning BMW Individual paint finishes. The colours available were initially Imola Red, Santorini Blue and Mineral White. BMW later added some other colours from their Individual colour palette. This car's colour of Stratus Grey makes it one of the rarest available.

The interior of the LE500 features full black Novillo leather upholstery that has blue highlight stitching. The black leather is matched to a Piano black high gloss interior trim.

Other design features that mark out an LE500 from a regular M3 are the 19" Gloss Black M Double Spoke Alloy Wheels, Gloss Black Kidney Grills and the laser etched 1 0f 500 plaque on the passenger side dash trim.

All of the enhancements carried out on the LE500 are visual which is not a bad thing. It means you still get the legendary S65 4.0L NA V8 engine and as per this car the 7-Speed M-DCT twin-clutch gearbox with steering wheel mounted gear shift paddles.

BMW were also very generous when it came to standard equipment on the LE500. It featured many options that would have meant ticking a few boxes on a standard car. These include Front & Rear Parking Sensors, Professional Multi-Media Sat-Nav and Heated Front Seats.

The E92 M3 was replaced in 2014 by the F80 M3. The new car featured a 3.0L 6-Cylinder Twin Turbo engine that was faster, had more power and more torque. But what it gained in statistics it lost in soul and emotion. Many car enthusiasts see the E92 M3 as a high point in the history of the M3 family. It was the only car to feature a V8 engine, the first to use the M-DCT gearbox and last normally aspirated car.

Although this car is only 9 years old it can now be considered a classic. Prices for the E92 M3 are on the rise and when you throw in a limited-edition model in a BMW Individual colour you could well see this car as an investment.

Vehicle provenance and history are very important to a car that enjoys such a following as the E92 M3. This car was supplied on-island by Buchanan BMW and features a full-service history to back up its mileage of 47,356 miles.

If you are looking for a usable modern classic car that you can drive every day or keep for special occasions look no further.

Title: 2017 Volkswagen Transporter T6 T32 2.0 TDI BMT 150 Highline Kombi SWB
Model: Transporter T6 T32 2.0 TDI BMT 150 Highline Kombi SWB
Description:
SkillanNaylor Car Company are pleased to offer this 2017 Volkswagen Transporter T6 T32 2.0 TDI BMT 150 Highline Kombi SWB seen in Indium Grey with Anthracite Cloth upholstery.

Do you know what was the best selling vehicle in the UK in 2022? It was the Ford Transit. That's right a van out sold any car from any sector. This shows you how popular driving a van is.

You would expect that most vans are bought by tradesmen and you would be right however more and more people are buying vans as there primary vehicle. This is because driving a van offers so much more space and flexibility than your average family car.

When people buy a van to use as the daily driver what motivates them to chose a particular make or model can differ. Some just want a workhorse and are not bothered by who the manufacture is as long as they can get their stuff in it. At the other end of the spectrum you have people who are fanatically loyal to one make & model. This usually means you are either a Ford Transit driver or Volkswagen Transporter driver.

A lot of other car manufacture use the VW Golf as measuring stick to compare their own cars against. "It drives like a Golf" is a phrase often used when talking about a rival model. This is the same when it comes to vans. The Transit drives like a Transit. By this i mean well but you can still tell it is a commercial vehicle. A Transporter drives like a Golf. They are refined, quiet, well built and comfortable.

With the rise in the sales of vans has seen also seen the rise in companies offering to upgrade and modify them. Have a look online. There is whole new industry booming with the supply of new wheels, body kits, interiors and performance upgrades for vans.

If you enjoy an active family life style a 'Kombi' van is the most popular choice. A Kombi van is a van with additional side windows and a second row of seats. This adds to the flexibility as it means you can carry all of your stuff and your family at the same time. Most Kombi vans have the ability to remove the second row of seats should you on occasion need to increase the carrying capacity.

This Volkswagen Transporters is T6 which means it is one of the latest models. (There is now a T6.1 which feature a revised front end design and upgraded dashboard). The T32 designation means that this van is design to carry heavy loads. There are over lower models available referred to as T26,28,30.

The engine in this van is a 2.0L 4-Cylinder Turbo Diesel that develops 150 BHP. This gives the van car like pace along with decent fuel economy and running costs.

Highline is the trim level and in this van it means you get rear parking sensors, a heated windscreen, electric folding door mirrors and Bluetooth phone & music prep. These option again add to the car like feel. We have give this van a visual upgrade by adding genuine VW Transporter 18" Satin Black Sportline Alloy Wheels.

As mentioned a lot of vans are bought for commercial purposes. This van stands out as it has only be used for non commercial use from day one. This shows in its excellent condition both inside and out. The condition is further backed up by its extremely low mileage of just 14,916 miles.

One final and important feature about this van is the price. If it was a commercially used van the price would be plus VAT. As this was a privately used vehicle the VAT was paid by the first own and is now not due.

If you want a vehicle that is as good to look at as it is to drive that offers ultimate practicality look no further.

Title: 2018 BMW X5 xDrive30d M-Sport 5Dr Auto
Description:
SkillanNaylor Car Company are pleased to offer this 2018 BMW X5 xDrive30d M-Sport 5Dr Auto seen in Space Grey Metallic with Black Dakota Leather upholstery.

The BMW X5 was first introduced back 1999. Some people say that the BMW X5 created the Sports Utility Vehicle segment aka SUV. When BMW designed the X5 it was within the era the BMW owned Land Rover. Land Rovers back catalogue of off-road tech was raided to make the X5 and many parts of the BMW are shared with the Range Rover (L322) of the same period.

What is an SUV? According to Wikipedia it is a car classification that combines elements of road-going passenger cars with features from off-road vehicles, such as raised ground clearance and four-wheel drive. The term SUV has been applied to the Nissan Qashqai and Bentley Bentayga and everything in-between. In recent years of all the car segments available from all car manufactures it is the SUV sector that has seen the most growth. One thing about the SUV sector that is worth remembering and that is there is a difference between an 'off-road' vehicle and an 'all-terrain' vehicle. Most SUVs are all-terrain vehicles. If you constantly drive off-road buy an original Land Rover Defender.

The BMW X5 has always given the driver the feel of a sports focused German saloon car on stilts. Unlike other high-sided vehicles the X5 displays hardly any roll when pushed through a corner. Once you've driven an X5 its easy to see why BMW is known as the builder of 'The Ultimate Driving Machines'.

This is a third generation model X5 known as an F15. The majority of its tech is shared with the BMW 5 & 7 Series. Like the model before it this X5 is available with 7-Seats. When not in use the third row can be laid flat in the boot area so not impacting on the boot space. The middle row can be folded or tilted forward to aid access in to the rear of the vehicle and to give an equal amount of leg room for all of the rear passengers. Once adjusted the X5 will accommodate 7 adults.

This X5 is a 30d model which means its is powered by a 3.0L 6-Cylinder Turbo Diesel engine that develops 258 BHP. This offers great pace and acceptable MPG. Its also worth noting the currently 12 months IoM road tax is £305 which is very fair considering this vehicles weighs approximately 2 tons.

The F15 X5 is offered in two trim levels either SE or like this car M-Sport. M-Sport gives you body styling and chassis set up inspired by BMW M. You get fully colour coded body work and a pretty set of 20" M Double Spoke Alloy Wheels. You also get self levelling air-suspension so even though you have a large set of wheels the ride quality is also still very good.

As with any German car the standard specification is generous as is the ability to add some factory options. In this car they included a 360 Camera System, a Harman Kardon Stereo and Head-Up Display. This feature projects information relating to the car such as the vehicle speed, Sat-Nav and radio directly on to the Windscreen.

This car was supplied new on island to its one former keep and it has covered a very low mileage of just 22,035 miles. It is presented in excellent condition through out and with a full service history.

To summarise if you enjoy driving but need to carry the family around too this could be just the car for you.

Title: 2020 BMW X3 xDrive M40i 5Dr Auto
Description:
SkillanNaylor Car Company are pleased to offer this 2020 BMW X3 xDrive M40i 5Dr Auto seen in Phytonic Blue Metallic with Black Vernasca Leather featuring Blue highlight stitching.

The BMW X3 has been in production now for 20 years. It was first launched back in 2003 and designed to sit below the BMW X5 in both size and cost. The X3 has always been a good car to drive however with the generation one car, code named E83 you could tell that it had been built to a price so as not to compete with the X5. The choice of some interior plastics wasn't great and it was never given all of the features & options that were available on the X5. The gen one car (E83) was available with a choice of both petrol and diesel engines with either a 2.0L 4-Cylinder or 3.0L 6-Cylinder capacity. There were the usual trim levels of SE, Sport and in later cars M-Sport.

In 2010 BMW launched the second generation X3 coded named F25. This brought through many improves to the model. The overall quality was much better and the visual aesthetics were much cleaner thanks to more colour coding of the bodywork. In the UK the F25 variant of the X3 was available with diesel power only in either 2.0L 4-Cylinder Turbo diesel form know as a 20d or with a 3.0L 6-Cylinder diesel engine. The 3.0L engine could be had with either one turbo, 30d or with two turbos, 35d. The 35d range topping model was a great car. It developed 313 BHP and 630Nm Torque. The trim levels in the F25 X3 were similar to the original car. You could have SE, X-Line and M-Sport.

in 2017 BMW debuted the all-New G01 variant of the X3. With this car the X3 was let of the leash. It no longer had to try and sit below its bigger brother the X5. There were no compromises made in the construction or specification of the new X3. The cabin was made of the best materials which included lots of soft-touch plastics and luxurious leather. The engine range now included petrol models again and for the first time their was a BMW M model.

This BMW X3 is an M40i. This means it is classed as an M Performance model or M lite. It features a 3.0L 6-Cylinder Turbo petrol engine that develops 382 HP. Until the X3M was launched a couple of years later this was the most powerful X3 ever built. Like all X3's the engine is connected to BMW's xDrive 4-Wheel Drive system and through an 8-Speed sports auto gearbox.

The M40i model of X3 comes with a very high level of factory equipment. This includes Adaptive M-Suspension, larger brakes with Blue Callipers and a Multi-Media touchscreen infotainment system that features Professional Sat-Nav and Apple Car Play.

As with any German car you can also raid the factory options list and add a host of other options. On this car the first owner picked just about everything available. The options include Head-Up Display which projects information such as the Sat-Nav and vehicle speed directly on to the Windscreen. This car also has a Harman Kardon Stereo and a Gesture Opening & Closing Power Tailgate. This means you can open or close the tailgate by waving your foot under the rear bumper. This an invaluable feature when trying to load the boot with your hands full.

Car manufactures can sometimes be associated with certain colours e.g. Red Ferrari's and Silver Mercedes. For BMW their signature colour has to be blue. This car is finished in a stunning shade of blue called Phytonic Blue Metallic. This is complimented by a full black leather interior which features blue highlight stitching.

This car was sold new by us in December 2020 to its one former keep. It has cover an incredibly low mileage of just 2,896 miles, that's right just 2,896 miles and as such is presented in as new condition. If you want a new car at pre-owned money this could be just the car for you.

Title: 2015 Mercedes SLK 250 CDI 2Dr Tip Auto Roadster
Description:
SkillanNaylor Car Company are pleased to offer this 2015 Mercedes SLK 250 CDI 2Dr Tip Auto Roadster seen in Obsidian Black with Black Leather upholstery.

USP - Unique Selling Point. When a car has a USP over other similar cars it should have more appeal. When Mercedes launched the SLK it was the first two seat roadster to feature a folding metal roof. This meant that when the roof was up the SLK just felt like a two seat coupe. The roof can be lowered or raised at the touch of a button and without a clips or clasps to be released.

In 2009 BMW launched the second generation Z4 and this too featured a folding metal roof. Mercedes SLK had lost its USP. How could Mercedes now differentiate the SLK from the Z4? The now unique element of the SLK was  its engine range which now included a diesel option. BMW did not off the Z4 with a diesel motor and the Porsche Boxster was also petrol only.

With the Mercedes SLK 250 CDI you got roof down motoring and low running costs. The engine in the SLK 250 CDI is a 2.1L 4-Cylinder Turbo Diesel that develops 204 BHP and 500 Nm torque. This gives the car excellent all round performance & efficiency. 0-62 MPH takes just 6.7 Secs whilst still returning 56 MPG (Combined).

The Mercedes SLK does have another feature that has since been copied by other manufactures of convertible cars and that is its Airscarf system. This feature blows hot air from a vent in the top of the seats and around the neck of the driver & passenger. This creates a warm environment which means that the car can be enjoyed with the roof down on any sunny day throughout the year.

This SLK 250 CDI is presented in excellent condition which backs up its very low mileage of just 18,829 miles. If you are looking for some roof down motoring in a car that won't cost the earth to run look no further.

Title: 2018 Lexus NX300h 2.5 SE (Premium Nav) 5Dr Auto
Description:
SkillanNaylor Car Company are pleased to offer this 2018 Lexus NX300h 2.5 SE (Premium Nav) 5Dr Auto seen in Mesa Red Metallic with Ebony Black Leather.

The Lexus NX is their offering in the mid-sized premium SUV sector. Its direct rivals would be BMW X1/X3, Mercedes GLA/B/C and Audi Q3/5. It size means it straddles two segment sizes e.g. bigger than a BMW X1 but not quite as big as a BMW X3.

Like all Lexus the NX is powered by a combination of hybrid petrol and electric. The hybrid system in the NX is described as a mild hybrid. This means that its ability to drive in purely electric power only is limited to slow speed driving such as Douglas Promenade or in busy town traffic. The flip side of this is that the batteries are charged up whilst you drive rather than through a cable when 'plugged in'. This means the faff sometimes associated with electric vehicles is gone.

The combination of the 2.5L 4-Cylinder engine and electric motor gives 197 BHP. This means you get decent performance and good MPG. The hybrid system is fully automatic and will switch between the two power units as and when required. It also make for a very smooth drive as once you come to rest at a halt sign and the car switches off once you are ready to drive off again the initial pick-up is taken car of by the electric motor. It then seamlessly switches over to the petrol engine once the speed increases.

Another element that the Lexus NX majors in is reliability. Lexus as a brand has always been at the very top of any reliability survey thanks to their excellent build quality and tried & tested hybrid technology.

The Lexus NX offers an elevated driving position, good visibility and a specious luxurious cabin. Thanks to its 4-Wheel drive system the Lexus NX performances well in adverse weather and has limited all-terrain driving ability.

This Lexus NX is an SE Premium Nav model. This means it is equipped with features and options that include heated front seats, reversing assist camera and a wide screen sat-nav system.

Presented in excellent condition throughout and with just 37,595 miles this car is ready to go.
