Title: 2020 MINI Electric 135kW Level 3 3Dr Auto
Description:
SkillanNaylor Car Company are pleased to offer this 2020 MINI Electric 135kW Level 3 3Dr Auto seen in Midnight Black Metallic with MINI Yours Carbon Black Lounge Leather upholstery.

The MINI 3Dr hatchback has always been big on personality. The endless combinations of colour, trim and options means that you really can personalise the car to suit your own style. Whether that is bold bright body colours paired with a contrasting roof colour or a black, grey or silver body colour matched to a black leather upholstery interior you can't really go wrong.

When BMW relaunched the MINI brand back in 2000 they overnight created the premium small hatchback sector. Audi soon launched the A1 as a competitor however it fails to match the MINI for individuality and overall fun. The MINI can also call back on a history stretching all the way back to 1959 and the original Alec Issigonis MINI which is now considered a design icon.

MINI's are bought by people from all walks of life whether they be new young drivers, older people, companies, individuals etc. Its very hard to stereotype or pigeon hole a car with a person or circumstance. What MINI's are best at is blasting around town. They are easy to drive and park thanks to the diminutive size but you never feel intimidated or exposed thanks to the solid build and big car feel.

MINI has always offered the 3Dr hatch with a range of both petrol and diesel engines that develop different levels of power. From the MINI One that puts out around 100 BHP and is the weapon of choice for new drivers thanks to its low insurance group all the way up to the JCW model that has 227BHP and its comfortable on the street or track.

You could say that MINI is a heritage brand thanks to its long history making cars. In 2020 MINI moved with the times and launch the MINI Electric 3Dr hatchback. This is a MINI that looks just like any other but is in fact powered purely by electric. To do this MINI had to hide the batteries somewhere. The get around this packaging conundrum they very cleverly put the batteries in the floor of the MINI. If you park a MINI Electric next to a normal petrol or diesel powered car you will see that the electric powered car is about 5cm taller. If you didn't know it was an electric car you would never guess it was.

I think this cleaver design is a real win for MINI. Many car manufactures feel they need to restyle their electric cars so that people know that they are driving. This can lead to some awkward designs that try to hard to be futuristic.

This MINI Electric is referred to as a Level 3. All MINI Electric share the same battery capacity, motor and range. The level number references the equipment the car has with 3 being the top specification. This car is equipped with features & options that include a panoramic glass sunroof, Apple Car Play, heated front seats, head-up display and a reversing assist camera.

The MINI Electric is powered by a 135kW motor that is equivalent to 184 BHP. It has a manufacture range of 145 miles and if you plugged it in to a charger located on Douglas promenade 3 hours charging would give you approximately 100 miles range at a cost of £6.

The fact that this car is powered by electric does not detract from its core mission to offer go-kart like handling and maximum fun. It actually enhances the performance thanks to the instant torque offered by the electric motor.

We supplied this car to its one former owner when new. It has covered just 15,014 miles and is presented in great condition throughout.

If you want an electric car that doesn't look like an electric car, that has a great specification and good looks then this could be just the car for you.

Title: 2019 Porsche 718 Cayman 2.5 S 2Dr PDK Auto
Description:
SkillanNaylor Car Company are pleased to offer this 2019 Porsche 718 Cayman 2.5 S 2Dr PDK Auto seen in Anthracite Satin Grey (Carrera White) with Black Leather upholstery.

The Porsche Cayman was first launched back in 2005. It is the sister car to the Porsche Boxster and has a 2-Door fixed roof body rather than a folding soft-top as per the Boxster. Unlike its bigger brother the Porsche 911 the engine in the Cayman is placed in the middle of the chassis rather than at the back like the 911. This endows the car with great handling and an overall more neutral balance.

Like any car that has been in production for almost 20 year the Cayman has gone through quite an evolutionary phase of improvement. The original car from 2005 was referred to as a 987 and this had a traditional Porsche Flat-6 Boxer engine ranging from 2.7L - 3.2L. In 2012 Porsche debuted the 981 version of the Cayman. The format stayed quite similar to the original car however the engine sizes grey to 2.9L and 3.4L. Unlike the 911 the 987 and 981 code numbers were not used to describe the Cayman, it was simply known by is name.

In 2016 Porsche launched the all-New 718 Cayman. This was a seismic shift compared to the earlier cars. 718 was now used as the name for the car and the for the first time the number was adorned on to the body. The silhouette of the car still resembled the previous models. Its still looked like a Cayman. It was what was under the skin that was wildly different.

The engine was still placed in the midship of the car but it was no longer a normally aspirated Flat-6 Boxer. The 718 used an all-New and unique to the model Flat-4 Boxer Turbo Petrol engine. The change of engine configuration met with a mixed response from Porsche enthusiasts.

If you go online you will find some negativity towards the Flat-4 Boxer Turbo engine. Most of this is from Porsche fanboys who have never driven a 718 Cayman. "It does sound the same", "It does sound like a Porsche", "It doesn't rev like a Porsche". These are the sort of comments you will find.

These comments are correct however what they don't say is that the all-New Flat-4 Boxer Turbo is more powerful, more torquey, produces less C02 and offers better MPG. In this Cayman S the engine size is 2.5L, it produces 350 BHP and just 167 g/Km C02 which equates to an annual Isle of Man Road Tax cost of just £274. If you compare these stats to an older 981 3.4L Flat-6 Boxer you will see that the 718 is much improved. The 718 still sound very good, just not like a 981. The engine is very modern and features and direct fuel injection, variable turbo turbine geometry and dry-sump lubrication.

The engine in this car is connected to what Porsche call a PDK auto gearbox. PDK is an abbreviation for Porsche-Doppelkupplungsgetriebe, which can be translated in to English as Porsche double-clutch transmission. You have two clutches. One that looks after the odd numbers i.e. 1, 3, 5, 7 and a second clutch that does the even numbers i.e. 2, 4 and 6. What this means is that when you change gear the gearbox via the second clutch has already pre-loaded the required gear. This means that nit only are the shifts very smooth but also lightning fast. You can let the car change gear in normal auto mode or do it yourself via the steering wheel mounted gear shift paddles.

When you 'spec-up' a Porsche new you will see that they are the masters of additional, paid for factory options. Almost all of the features you can see or touch will be an option from the alloy wheel style & size to the upholstery fabric. Thankfully on this car the original owner wasn't scared to tick a few boxes. This car has features & options that include 20" Carrera Classic Alloy Wheels, Sport Chrono Pack, Heated Front Seats and PCM - Porsche Communication Modula (Sat-Nav).

Unlike some other premium car manufactures Porsche is not scared to offer their cars in some very bright colours e.g. Speed Yellow, Lizard Green and Ruby Stone (a sort of pink). Sometimes however owners want their cars to standout in a different way. The previous owner of this car chose to have its classic Carrera White paintwork wrapped in Anthracite Satin Grey. The quality of the wrap is extremally good and it does extend into the majority of the door shuts which gives a factory painted appearance. It is also protecting the paint work underneath from damage so if the new owner decided to remove it at a later stage the car would look factory fresh.

This car is presented in fine order throughout and with just 22,457 miles. The next annual service will be completed prior to delivery and the car will come with a comprehensive warranty.

To summaries if you want a sports car that is stunning to look at and drive, that subtilty stands out from the crowd and won't cost the earth to run this could be just the car for you.

Title: 2015 Porsche Cayenne 4.8 Turbo S Tiptronic S
Description:
SkillanNaylor Car Company are pleased to offer this 2015 Porsche Cayenne 4.8 Turbo S Tiptronic S seen in Jet Black Metallic with Black/Cream Extended Leather upholstery.

To many the Porsche Cayenne Turbo S is the ultimate SUV. When this car was produced there was nothing else that offered the combination of luxury and speed available in the Cayenne Turbo S. The headline figures for this car are 562 BHP, 800 Nm Torque and 0-62 MPH in just 4.1 Secs. Today those statistics would shame many so called 'Super cars'.

In 2015 the other German car manufactures all offered high performance SUVs. BMW has the X5M, Audi had the SQ7 and Mercedes had the GLE 63 AMG. All three of these cars are excellent in their own right. With Porsche its the last 20% that they seem to be able to do better than their competitors. This improvement is not limited to a performance gain. The X5 and GLE will match the power of the Turbo S. Its things like the width of the steering wheel rim, the feel of the gear selector and the touch of the dash buttons. On a Porsche everything feels mechanical. It feels very well engineered and ergonomically perfect.

The other advantage that Porsche offers its customers is the ability to choose and design their perfect car. All car manufactures have an online car configurator on their website so that you can build the car to the specification you want. Porsche has always offered the customer more opportunities to change items of the car. This can be exterior colours, interior trims or individual factory options. The original owner of this car chose items such as a leather/carbon fibre steering wheel, Alcantara roof headlining, a Burmester Surround Sound Stereo and Professional Rear Seat Entertainment including 2 x screens.

Porsche is known as a build of some of the finest sports cars in the world. Some would say the the Porsche 911 is 'the' sports car that defines the sector. Lessons learned through many years of car racing have been used to set-up and equip the Cayenne Turbo S with some of the best hardware to make it handle like no other tall sided SUV has the right to. Porsche also loves their acronyms to describe the features that are used to make the Cayenne Turbo handle so well.

  • PCCB - Porsche Carbon Ceramic Brakes
  • PDCC - Porsche Dynamic Chassis Control
  • PASM - Porsche Active Suspension Management
  • PSM - Porsche Stability Management
  • PTV - Porsche Torque Vectoring

To signify that the Cayenne Turbo S sits at the top of the ultimate SUV table are a few other features that you again associate with a Supercar. These would be the 10-Piston Callipers that grab the 420mm Carbon Ceramic Brakes. The switchable sports exhaust that has a valve in it that lets you change how loud the car is and the 21" Forged Turbo Alloy Wheels.

Owning a car like this is about excess. Excessive performance, excessive specification and excessive luxury. If you are looking for car with good MPG and low road tax this is not the car for you. If you want to embarrasses Supercars whilst carrying all of the family and their luggage then look no further.

This is a local car from new and is offered in excellent condition throughout. It has covered 51,968 miles and benefits from a full service history.

Title: 2017 MINI 2.0 John Cooper Works Challenge 3Dr
Description:
SkillanNaylor Car Company are pleased to offer this 2017 MINI 2.0 John Cooper Works Challenge 3Dr seen in White Silver Metallic with Anthracite Cloth/Alcantara upholstery.

John Cooper Works is the performance sub brand for MINI. John Cooper Works or JCW cars are the fastest most focused variants of the MINI range.

The MINI JCW 3DR Hatch is a great car and regarding as a potent hot hatch. It features a 2.0L 4-Cylinder Turbo Petrol engine that develops 227 BHP. This amount of power in a car the size and weight of a 3Dr MINI makes for an exciting ride.

In 2017 EVO Magazine asked the questions " What if the MINI JCW 3Dr was made even more focused and exciting to drive. What if the chassis and running gear were upgraded with the very best hardware available. Could the MINI JCW 3Dr Hatch be made into a track warrior capable of slaying much more powerful and expensive circuit monsters?"

The MINI JCW Challenge was a collaboration between EVO magazine and MINI UK. It was a 'Skunk Works' project that almost didn't happen. This was due to MINI's parent company BMW not being in favour of using third-party upgrade parts. They thought that only parts developed by them should be used to improve the MINI JCW 3Dr Hatch.

MINI UK & EVO won the arm wrestle and the New MINI JCW Challenge was given the green light. Its development was covered in a few editions of EVO magazine and input of the chassis dynamics came from the journalists who worked for EVO at the time. The whole car was gone through and stiffened and lightened where required. The factory specification was paired down and no other options were available to be added. The non-MINI upgrades read like a who's who of the performance car world. Nitron, Team Dynamics, Pirelli, Mintex, Quaife were all called upon to enhance and upgrade the MINI.

There was supposed to be a planned build run of 100 cars however only 53 were ever completed. This makes the JCW Challenge one of the rarest MINIs available. Of the cars produced approximately half a driven and the other half are in car collections.

The MINI JCW Challenge is track focused pocket rocket that cares little for refinement and more about lap times. It does however still offer some creature comforts. It has seating for 4 adults unlike the GP MINI's that were reduced to just 2 seats. It has Bluetooth phone prep, rear parking sensors and even ISOFIX Child Seat prep.

This car is number 12 and it has just 21,484 miles and is presented in great condition throughout. If you are looking for a hardcore track toy that can also be driven day to day that will embarrass most supercars that cost 3 x as much look no further.

Title: 2015 MINI Clubman 2.0 Cooper S 6Dr Auto
Description:
SkillanNaylor Car Company are pleased to offer this 2015 MINI Clubman 2.0 Cooper S 6Dr Auto seen in Melting Silver Metallic with a contrasting Midnight Black Roof & Mirror Caps and Carbon Black Leather upholstery.

When you think of the MINI brand it is the classic three door body type that first comes to mind. Depending on your age it will either by the 1959 Sir Alec Issigonis original or the BMW MINI which was relaunched back in 2000.

The MINI 3Dr hatchback remains the brands core car however in the past when people wanted something a bit bigger it usually meant leaving the brand and buying something else.

In 2007 MINI launched the all-New MINI Clubman. If you are familiar with the historic back catalogue of original MINI's this mini estate body style was called a Traveller. The new BMW/MINI brand did not own the rights to reuse this name so choose Clubman which not to confuse you further was originally used by MINI when the facelifted the original 3Dr car with a flat front design.

The all-New MINI Clubman was a stretched version of the 3Dr and had approximately a 50% bigger boot and 50% more rear leg room. To aid access in to the back of the car the MINI Clubman had a unique single door on the off-side of the car that opened backwards aka in a Suicide fashion. This did in deed grant better access to the rear of the car however having only one door that was on the other side to the pavement did throw up a few challenges for the owner. The all-New MINI Clubman did also have one other feature that tied it back to the original cars and that was the twin barn down style opening for the boot area. This was a good if not a little quirky idea as it meant you could keep on door closed and the other open when getting items from the boot.

As mentioned the MINI Clubman was based upon a stretched eversion of the 3Dr hatchback. It was more practical than the 3Dr hatch but not really a competitor to the likes of the VW Golf or Audi A3. To meet the other premium hatchbacks head-on MINI would have to evolve the Clubman to another level.

The generation one MINI Clubman stayed in production until 2014 before it was replaced by a ground-up new car. All BMW/MINI products have a code name. The generation one Clubman was an R55. The all-New generation two is referred to as an F54. The F54 Clubman was based upon a platform that was shared with the New MINI Countryman and also the BMW X1, X2,  2 Series Active Tourer and Grand Tourer. This move of platform to a BMW not only meant that the car was overall larger the quality of the build and technology available was much higher. This move also meant that the body shape could be a little bit more traditional. Most hatchbacks are either 3 or 5 door body styles. The MINI Clubman is referred to as a 6-Door hatchback as it has two forward opening doors on each side and like the gen 1 cars tow barn style opening doors at the rear.

The size of the gen 2 MINI Clubman is close to a BMW 1 Series, Audi A3 Sportback or VW Golf. Its long roof make it look like a mini estate car however its really a hatchback with a different rear door arrangement.

MINI offer the Clubman in a wide range of both petrol and diesel engines and trim levels. This Clubman is a Cooper S model which means it has a 2.0L 4-Cylinder Turbo Petrol engine that develops 190 BHP. In this car it is connected to an 8-Speed Sports Auto Gearbox. To go with different trim levels there are a number of packs also available. The hotter the pack the better the spec. This car benefits from a CHILI pack which is obviously the hottest available.

This MINI Clubman was supplied new on-island by Buchanan MINI and it features a full service history to back up its very low mileage of just 19,541 miles.

When you order a New MINI it is blank canvas affair. Due to the amount of factory options available it is said that no two MINI's are exactly the same. This car has an extensive specification and features some options that you don't see on a MINI very often such as electric/memory/heated front seats.

In conclusion if you want a great specification, low mileage, premium car that has a quirky edge and lots of personality look no further.

Title: 2014 Porsche Cayenne S 4.1 Diesel 5Dr Tiptronic Auto
Description:
SkillanNaylor Car Company are pleased to offer this 2014 Porsche Cayenne S 4.1 Diesel 5Dr Tiptronic Auto see in Carrera White with Black Leather upholstery.

Porsche debuted the all-New Cayenne over 20 years ago back in 2002. This was a controversial move and car. It was so far removed from any Porsche that had come before it that most Porsche enthusiasts didn't get it, didn't like it and didn't want to drive it. Porsche was renowned for building rear engined sports cars not two ton SUV's. Porsche enthusiasts thought that the Cayenne was cynical marketing excise to grab a piece of the fast growing SUV sector. The other negative element that effected the Cayenne was that it shared many of its components with the VW Touareg and Audi Q7. Porsche were not know for 'platform sharing' and the thought that a Porsche was really a VW/Audi did not sit well with some buyers.

All of the above is true however is was also all before anyone had driven the new Porsche Cayenne. Once you saw the car and got behind the steering wheel there was no doubt that this car was a true Porsche. All of the design cue's associated with other Porsche models were there. The 5 hooded dials located in the dash brinicle like every other Porsche are located on the dash. The wide sculptured wheel arches housing large alloy wheels and the front bumper with gapping air cooling ducts are all part of the design.

The Cayenne may weight two tons however it never felt this heavy and always masked its weight and mass very well. The engine range has always been strong and goes from a 3.0L V6 to a 4.8L V8 twin Turbo petrol. Porsche did also offer the Cayenne with a choice of two diesel engines. 3.0L V6 Turbo and like this car 4.1L V8 Twin Turbo.

The comments about the Porsche Cayenne being a cynical marketing excise were true in the sense that it attracted lots of new buyers to the brand. If you owned a Porsche 911 but also wanted a family car or SUV usually meant looking at something from an other brand. Now you could have a car from Porsche.

The Cayenne went on to be a huge success for Porsche and was consistently their top selling model. The sales of Cayenne's meant that Porsche could use the money created by this model to further develop the 911's, Boxster's and Cayman's. Without the Cayenne Porsche might not of survived as a brand. Its thanks to the Cayenne that Porsche is such a good place now.

This Porsche Cayenne is a second generation 'S' model. This sits it in the middle of the range in terms of specification and performance. This car is powered by a 4.1L V8 Twin Turbo Diesel engine and what an engine it is. It develops 385 BHP but more importantly 850 Nm torque. As a publicity stunt on 1 May 2017, a 2017 Porsche Cayenne S Diesel set the Guinness World Record for heaviest aircraft pulled by a production car. The Cayenne towed a 265-tonAirbus A380 to a distance of 42 meters, breaking the previous 2013 record set by a Nissan Patrol.

As with any Porsche the base specification is exactly that...'basic'! When you are ordering and 'spec'ing' a New Porsche it is usually a blank canvas affair. There is a vast range of factory features and options to choose from. On this car it would appear that most of the available boxes were ticked. The specification of this car includes PASM - Porsche Active Suspension Management, BOSE Stereo, a Panoramic Glass Sunroof, Adaptive, Heated, Memory Front Seats, 21" 911 Turbo II Style Alloy Wheels and Deployable Tow-Bar just in case you wanted to tow any aircraft! It also worth noting that although this car can tow a plane its running costs are not sky high. 12 months Isle of Man road tax is £372 which is very fair considering its performance capabilities.

The other decision a person must make when ordering their new Porsche is the colour combination. The Cayenne has always been offered in a very subdued palette of different shades of grey, dark blue or black. This car stands out thanks to its gleaming Carrera White paintworks and contrasting full black leather upholstery.

To conclude if you are in the market for a great looking SUV with a very high specification and monster powertrain that can literally tow an aircraft look no further.

Title: 2017 BMW X4 xDrive20d M-Sport 5Dr Auto
Description:
SkillanNaylor Car Company are pleased to offer this 2017 BMW X4 xDrive20d M-Sport 5Dr Auto seen in Titanium Silver Metallic with Black Nevada Leather upholstery.

SAC - Sports Activity Coupe. What is an SAC? An SAC is a vehicle based upon an SUV - Sports Utility Vehicle but with a biased towards a more sporty appearance and dynamic drive. BMW were the first manufacture to have a vehicle in the SAC sector when they launched the X6 back in 2008.

When the BMW X6 was first launched it was a little misunderstood. Why would you want a less practical X5? The X6 was still very practical. It had a large boot and could accommodate 5 adults but being practical was not its main aim.

The BMW X6 looked dramatic and like no other car on the road. It had an elevated driving position and a higher ride height but had the roof silhouette of a sports coupe. It had some all-terrain driving ability but on-road it felt like a high-powered German saloon car.

The X6 proved very popular for BMW and soon other car manufactures had cars within the SAC sector. Mercedes had the GLC & GLE, Audi had the Q5 Sportback and Q8 and Porsche launched a coupe version of their Cayenne model. BMW too expanded their presences in the SAC segment and launched the X4 and X2 models. Both being similar in concept to the X6 just a little smaller.

This BMW X4 is a xDrive20d M-Sport model. This means it is equipped with BMW's xDrive permanent 4-wheel drive system and a 2.0L 4-Cylinder Turbo Diesel engine that develops 190 BHP. The trim level in this X4 is called M-Sport. This means it has body styling and chassis dynamics inspired by BMW's M department.

Like any premium German manufactured car the specification is very important. This car features factory options that include the M-Sport Plus Package, Interior Comfort Package and the very rare option of an Electric Glass Sunroof.

This BMW X4 looks great, drives well and has a generous equipment level however its standout feature is its extremely low mileage of just 10,498 miles. This mileage is backed up by a full service history.

To summaries if you want the practicality of an SUV but the sporty appearance and drive of a coupe this BMW X4 could be just the car for you.

Title: 2017 Ford Kuga 2.0 TDCI Zetec AWD 5Dr Auto
Description:
SkillanNaylor Car Company are pleased to offer this 2017 Ford Kuga 2.0 TDCI Zetec AWD 5Dr Auto seen in Jet Black with Anthracite Cloth upholstery.

The Ford Kuga is their offering in the mid-sized volume SUV sector. Its main rivals would be the likes of the Toyota RAV4, Peugeot 3008 and Skoda Karoq. The Kuga is based on a platform shared with the Focus. To anyone that has driven a Ford before the Kuga will feel very familiar.

It has an elevated driving position, a spacious cabin and a large boot. Inside you get a cabin with great ergonomics and a generous amount of equipment. All of the usual safety equipment is present which includes a multitude of air-bags, crash protection and traction & stability control.

The Kuga has good body control and it has been set up with comfort in mind. It rides well and is very good to drive. This car is powered by a 2.0L 4-Cylinder Turbo Diesel engine that develops 150 BHP. This gives the car decent performance and good MPG. The engine in this car is connected to a 6-Speed automatic gearbox and on to an All-Wheel-Drive system which means the car remains good to drive even after the weather has deteriorated.

The trim level of this Kuga is called Zetec. This sits it in the middle of what's available and does mean the spec includes Fords SYNC 3 Infotainment system that includes Sat-Nav and Apple Car Play.

If you want a car that is a pleasure to drive, specious, frugal, practical and good value look no further.

Title: 2018 Toyota RAV4 2.5 VVTI Hybrid Excel Nav TSS 5Dr Auto
Model: RAV4 2.5 VVTI Hybrid Excel Nav TSS 5Dr Auto
Description:
SkillanNaylor Car Company are pleased to offer this 2018 Toyota RAV4 2.5 VVTI Hybrid Excel Nav TSS 5Dr Auto seen in Pearl White Metallic with Anthracite/Ivory Leather upholstery.

The Toyota RVA4 has now been in production for almost 30 years. From day one it has been praised for its build quality, reliability and ruggedness. RAV stands for 'Recreational Activity Vehicle'. This is a nod towards its intended purpose and target market buyer who typically wants a fun family vehicle that can cope with the school run and trips to the beach.

The competitor cars to the RVV4 would be the likes of the Honda CRV and Nissan X-Trail. All three are great cars and all three have a Japanese feel which is the use of hard plastics in the interior which whilst not feeling as luxurious as a German car are extremely well built and practical.

This Toyota RVA4 is a forth generation model and like most other modern Toyota's is a hybrid vehicle which means its power comes from both petrol and electric. Its USP over other petrol/electric cars is that Toyota's use a mild fully regenerative electric system which charges up whilst you drive and does not need to be 'plugged-in'. This cuts down on the faff which can be associated with other electric powered vehicles. Also due to its hybrid powertrain this car produces sub 120 g/Km C02 which means 12 months IoM road tax will be just £71.

Toyota offer the RAV4 in a variety of different trim levels. This car is an Excel Nav model which puts it towards the top of what is available. It has features & options that include front & rear parking sensors, a reversing assist camera, heated front seats, sat-nav and a powered tailgate.

The interior of the RAV4 is very spacious and entry is easy thanks to the elevated seating position. It also has a very large boot area and plenty of storage. The chassis set-up on the RAV4 offers great ride quality and comfortable drive.

Offered in excellent condition throughout and with a full service history to back up its 45,365 miles.

In summary if you want a well built spacious family car that is offers low running cars and renowned reliability look no further.

Title: 2016 Subaru WRX 2.5 STI Type UK 4Dr Saloon
Description:
SkillanNaylor Car Company are pleased to offer this 2016 Subaru WRX 2.5 STI Type UK 4Dr Saloon seen in Glacier White Metallic with Anthracite Cloth/Alcantara upholstery.

All forms of motorsport have their golden eras. Formula One had Senna/Prost. British Touring Cars had Jason Plato/Matt Neal. In the World Rally Championship many would say the Colin McRae/Tommy Makinen era provided the best cars & drivers.

The phrase 'Race on Sunday, sell on Monday' could definitely be applied to the cars from the WRC. You were either a Tommy/Mitsubishi Evo fan or a Colin/Subaru Impreza supporter.

To be competitive in the WRC car manufactures had to equip the road cars that the rally cars were based on with extreme body kits and large rear spoilers. This gave them an almost cartoon like appearance when compared to other standard road cars.

The Subaru Impreza had signature colour scheme of Mica Blue Metallic Paint and gold alloy wheels. If you wanted to give of a rally vibe white with black wheels as per this car is another good look.

Almost all cars that competed in the WRC had a 2.0L 4-Cylinder Turbo Petrol engine. The Subaru Impreza took a different route by using a 2.0L Flat-4 Boxer Turbo Petrol Engine. This endowed it with a good lump of extra torque and a unique sound.

When this Subaru was launched, they had dropped the name Impreza and were just using WRX. The engine was still a boxer configuration however the size had now grown to 2.5L. It now produced 300 HP. This particular model is an STI Type UK which means you get the larger rear spoiler and the 18" Alloy Wheels. Unlike other modern sports cars that rely solely on electronics to improve the performance and dynamics the WRX is able to utilise mechanical differentials to get the power to the road.

The Subaru WRX is a car that is designed to be driven. If you want refinement than this is probably not the car for you. This car loves to be driven hard on any road surface in any road or weather condition. It feels raw and the lessons learnt from many years in the WRC are very obvious.

This car is presented in fine order and with 42,476 miles.

Title: 2021 Dacia Duster 1.0 TCe 100 Bi-Fuel Comfort 5dr
Description:
SkillanNaylor Car Company are pleased to offer this 2021 Dacia Duster 1.0 TCe 100 Bi-Fuel Comfort 5dr seen in Anthracite Grey Metallic with Black Cloth upholstery.

Every year all car manufactures are tasked with reducing their overall C02 output. To do this almost all have developed and launched vehicles that are either hybrid petrol/diesel electric or full electric.

Dacia is often seen as quite a quirky car manufacture so to reduce their C02 output they decided to go down a different road. That road is dual fuel. A vehicle that is powered by two different types of liquid fuel. In this case LPG or Liquid Petroleum Gas.

LPG powered cars were once very popular when the government incentivised people to convert their petrol-powered cars over to LPG. It was a sort of right fuel at the wrong time situation. Time moved on and as mentioned car manufactures started to explore electric as the fuel of the future.

What are the benefits of an LPG powered car? The cost of any fuel can fluctuate but LPG usually tracks below the cost of regular Unleaded.  There is one downside to owning an LPG powered car and that is the availability of the fuel. One the Isle of Man Kaneens in Union Mills are the only supplier of LPG for cars.

Unlike a plug-in hybrid electric car that requires you to charge the car up when you want to use the electric power in an LPG once the tank is filled you can switch between the two fuel types by the flick of a switch.

The Duster is of a similar size to the Nissan Qashqai. It has seating for 5 adults and a good-sized boot. It has a raised driving position which gives the driver good visibility and ease of entry into the cabin. It has a rugged, chunky stance and good road presents.

From their launch Dacia have always been at the front of affordable motoring. Making an affordable car doesn't mean you miss out on some essential specification. This car benefits from features like Sat-Nav, a reversing assist camera and 16" Alloy Wheels.

This car represents excellent value as it is less than 12 months old and has just 1,719 miles showing. As you will appreciate it is presented in as-new condition.

Title: 2014 BMW 420i xDrive Luxury 2Dr Coupe Auto
Description:
SkillanNaylor Car Company are pleased to offer this 2014 BMW 420i xDrive Luxury 2Dr Coupe Auto seen in Black Sapphire Metallic with Black Dakota Leather.

The BMW 4 Series is the sister car to the BMW 3 Series. They share chassis, engines and interiors. The 4 Series is actually slightly longer and wider that the 3 Series and has a more flowing sporty appearance.

The BMW 4 Series is offered in a variety of different trim levels and engine configurations. This is a luxury model which means it has an elegant style compared to an M-Sport model. You get chrome exterior trim and non-sports suspension which is a blessing on some of our Manx roads.

This is a 420i model which means it is powered by a 2.0L 4-Cylinder Turbo Petrol engine that develops 184 BHP. The engine is connected to an 8-Speed Sports Auto Gearbox.

When the weather turns bad powerful, rear wheel drive cars do have an Achillies Heal and that is traction. In snow or ice your typical BMW will struggle. Not this car as it is an xDrive model which is BMW speak for 4-Wheel Drive.

The direct competitor cars to the BMW 4 Series Coupe would be the Audi A5 Coupe and Mercedes C Class Coupe. All are good cars however if you compare cars of the same age as this 2014 BMW you will find that the Infotainment system in the BMW is far superior to the other two German cars. The dash screen is larger, and the functionality is much better. The BMW also maintains its 'Ultimate Driving Machine' status and is overall more rewarding to drive.

Presented in Black Sapphire Metallic with matching Black Dakota Leather but with contrasting chrome exterior trim and silver alloy wheels this car looks every bit the classy German Coupe.

Offered with a low mileage for its age of 44,636 miles which is backed up by a full-service history.

Title: 2017 Lexus GS 300h 2.5 Luxury 4DR Auto
Description:
SkillanNaylor Car Company are pleased to offer this 2017 Lexus GS 300h 2.5 Luxury 4DR Auto seen in Champagne Silver Metallic with Black/Cream Leather upholstery.

The Lexus GS range is their offering in the mid-sided premium executive car sector. The rivals to the GS would be the BMW 5 Series, Mercedes E Class, Audi A6 and Jaguar XF. The fight for popularity within this sector is fierce. To standout a car needs to have a USP (Unique Selling Point). In the Lexus it is its petrol/electric hybrid powertrain. But hold on all of the German car manufactures also offer Hybrid vehicles.

The Lexus GS differs from its rivals because its petrol/electric hybrid engine is a self charging regenerative set-up. No plugging-in equals no faff. The car changes the batteries as it drives. When you slow down it automatically reverts to electric power. Once the speed increases it switches back to the petrol engine. This combination of petrol and electric gives a total of 223 BHP. This gives the car a car a good turn of speed but crucially a low amount of C02 and just 113 g/Km which equates to an Isle of Man annual road tax cost of just £71. Not to bad for a car of this size & weight.

As mentioned this car offers no faff motoring thanks to its hybrid engine set-up. Another thing that reduces the faff is this cars renowned reliability. Lexus has topped the JD Power most reliable car poll for the last 14 years.

The feel, fit and finish of the Lexus GS are typical Japanese. Well built, well thought out and with excellent ergonomics. The interior is dominated by the 12.3" Infotainment screen that displays the Sat-Nav, Media, Radio and Reversing Assist Camera. Electric/Memory/Heated/Cooled Front Seats, Elec Fold Ext Door Mirrors and Dual Zone Climate A/C are also part of the equipment list.

The body styling and visual appearance of the Lexus GS are again very Japanese and feature lots of sharp cuts and dramatic edges to the design. These sharp edges contrast against a soft, comfortable ride thanks to the comfort suspension set-up and 18" Alloy Wheels with generous tyre profiles.

This car is offered in excellent condition and with a low mileage of just 23,883 miles. This is complimented by a full service history.

If you want your cake and eat it e.g. Luxury performance with low running costs look no further.
